text:
does he love you, like i did?

yes, a common question that my heart still plunges, so i thought to ask you.
does he love you like i did?

does he love you as much as you love the smell of soil on first rain or as much as i love gazing you when you wink at me in front of folks.

i know he likes you as you are but he has not seen you dancing carelessly in front of the mirror. 
he must have seen your smile but not the weep you hide behind it.
he must have been there for you day and night but did he make you feel warmer on the cold midnight just by a call?
he knows how much sugar you need in your coffee but not the reasons i used to find only to have it with you.
i know he cares for you. but did he laugh at your pimple?
he praised you for your beauty but did he see you working hard for someone else?

my dear, he knows your outer shell, your mask, your prejudiced smile but doesn't know the pieces which you stored in your drenched heart. i think your preference for plastic over silk was successful.

maybe in this school of life you have learned the vulnerabilities of emotion.
and here i am, an illiterate who only knows how to write, say and mean just one word i.e 'love'
.
so before this exam starts getting tough.
don't forget my wishes are still there for you.

all the best.

darshan sanghvi.
(@darshansanghvi28)
.
.
.

text:
for my 17th birthday this year, i'm asking for donations to sexual assault center. i've chosen this nonprofit because one in five women and one in 71 men will be raped at some point in their lives. because every 98 seconds another american is sexually assaulted. because 99% of sexual violence perpetrators will walk free. because 94% of female sexual assault victims will experience ptsd throughout her lifetime. because one out of every 6 american women has been the victim of attempted or completed rape in her lifetime. because one in four girls and one in six boys will be sexually abused before they turn 18 years old. because i am one in four. because i am the 1 in 6. 
i hope you'll consider contributing. every little bit will help me reach my goal. i've included information about sexual assault center below.

to provide healing for children, adults, and families affected by sexual assault and to end sexual violence through counseling, education, and advocacy. they provide multiple therapy services to survivors and their loved ones. 
if you can’t donate, there is more you can do: prayer. pray for survivors. pray for our current law enforcement. pray for our judicial system. pray for the loved ones of survivors. pray for understanding of how horrific sexual assault and abuse is. pray. 
if you would be as kind to donate, the link is in my bio 💛 
#stopsexualabuse #stopsexualassault #metoo #1in6women #1in4girls #1in6boys #standup #speakout #every90seconds

text:
"believed him when he said he wasn’t like those other guys.
he didn’t have any tricks up his sleeves,
bad intentions.
she didn’t have to be worried this time.
but it didn’t take long for self-respecting girl to realize that that was just another line,
and of course, like many times before, she was fed just another lie.
like many times before she believed it...
like many times before, simple kisses turned into expectations.
she had to defend her right to have a right over her body.
explain why she didn’t want to be touched that way.
and that this wasn’t what she had in mind when he said, 'come back to mine.'"
~excerpt.

text:
#respetonaman is a nationwide campaign against gender-based violence. the goal of the project is to spark a sustainable movement across the nation to eliminate all forms of gender-based violence in the philippines through campaigning for awareness, empowerment, and policy.

as inspired by the global #metoo, and #timesup movement and thailand’s #donttellmehowtodress movement, it will focus on bringing the issue into the mainstream and empowering women to rise up against all forms of gender-based violence.

in line with this year's 16-days of activism against gender-based violence, #respetonaman will hold a series of events and programs which would include two big forums, an online campaign, and a localized version of the #donttellmehowtodress exhibit.

#respetonaman is a project of the office of vp @lenirobredo, @unwomen safe cities metro manila programme, the embassy of sweden in manila, @sparkphilippines, and empower; supported by donttellmehowtodress thailand, cindy sirinya bishop, bdo unibank, sanggunian ng mga paaralang loyola ng ateneo de manila, osci (office of social  concern and involvement of ateneo de manila university), and power plant mall.

text:
chimamanda adichie gets featured on the cover of the telegraph magazine.
⠀
on october 27th, the telegraph magazine featured nigerian author, chimamanda ngozi adichie on it's cover. in that feature, she discussed nigeria, misogyny, and the #metoo movement. chimamanda also talked about losing faith in nigeria after her father was kidnapped in 2015 and how she feels he was kidnapped because of her.⠀
⠀
below is an excerpt of the interview, in adichie's words:⠀
"it was because of me. that incident affected my father – it robbed him of something; there’s a distrust that he didn’t have before. he comes from a generation with a certain kind of integrity. for a long time he didn’t understand things like bribery – it just perplexed him. my father had given his everything – he got his phd in the us and he had job offers there in the 1960s, but he was keen to come back to nigeria. it was post-independence, everyone was very enthusiastic and my father spent his life teaching. i felt that nigeria had failed him – for a man of his age to be thrown into the boot of a car …that incident broke my heart and it’s the first time i started to seriously question nigeria."⠀
⠀

text:
patriarchy has become so much a part of our popular culture that not many of us dare to question that. almost all words in abusive language involve women, almost all adult jokes are sexist and you fear to break your “bro code” by interrupting in between those jokes even if you tend to think that it is wrong. you keep telling your sisters and your girlfriends about how “harami” men are and how women are better human beings but you do not dare to ask your male friends to be good human beings for the fear of being ostracised and left out. you have put a lot of onus on women to be good human beings and that is not fair. i must tell you that patriarchy is not doing any good to men either. it is a structure we all need to fight against, together. it is high time that we form an alliance.

there has been a lot of conversations around metoo lately, and you know what i am tired! it is high time that people stop putting the onus on women, they have done their part. they have come out and told their stories and many husbands, brothers and fathers were also shocked to hear the stories of their wives, sisters and daughters. the responsibility is now on men. they should really act now and should realise that bro code is not a thing to be proud of. start talking, engage in dialogue, ask your friends to behave properly, ask them not to objectify women if they say sexist jokes. it may seem weird and difficult to start interrupting your friends with whom you have been laughing on same sexist jokes for ages but you need to find your ways to deal with that. you need to talk and you need to express. be feminist, trust me it’s a good thing 🙂

you may think that why should you take that much pain, that you have not created the system of patriarchy and so the burden is not on you. you have not created but you are perpetuating it, promoting it. if you start acting now, if you start interrupting in between the sexist conversations now (no matter how difficult you find it on your masculinity); the world will be a better place in next 10 to 20 years. maybe your daughters won’t have such st

text:
نووسەر: شیرین @shirin_qurayshi 
زۆر قووڵ خەوتبووم، خەوێکی منداڵانەی پڕ لە ئارامی. لە ماڵێک کە هەمووی ماڵەکە تەنیا ژوورێک بوو و هیچی تر.
لە ناوەڕاستی بێستانێک کە تازە بڕکەکانی چەقەرەیان کردبوو، باوکم پێش ئەوەی بخەوین کووتی کە بەیانی زوو هەستین. کاتی بژار و تەنکە هاتووە! من لە کار نەدەترسام. مناڵێکی 6ساڵانی زۆر زیندوو بووم.. ئەوە قسەی دایکمە چون خۆم هیچم لە منداڵیم پێش ئەو شەوە لەبیر نەماوە.
بە جوڵانی شتێکی تەڕ لەسەر جەستەم چاوەکانم پچڕان لە عالەمی خەو. ترپەی دڵم ژوورەکەی کەڕ کرد. جەستەم کارەساتی بەسەر هاتبوو. چاوەکانم دوایین ئەندامی جەستەم بوون کە بە کارەساتی قەوماویان زانی.
ئەوەی من بینیم پیاوێک بوو کە لەسەر ئەژنۆ ڕای کردە ناو جێگاکە، کاتێک کە هەستی کرد چاوم کراوەتەوە. 
بەر چاوی من میچێکی قەڵەشیو بوو کە زۆر حەزم دەکرد بکەوێتە خوارەوە و لەو دڵەکووتەیە، لەو بێدەنگییە، لەو گەرمایە، لەو هەناسانەی تەقەلایان دەکرد بۆ هەوایەکەک کە نەبوو...
گەرمکونە خانەخانەکەی دایکم لە مەلاجامی مەهاباد بۆی کڕیبوومم پێش خەوتن لە پێدا بوو و ئێستا تا سەر ئەژنۆ داکێشرابوو! دەمزانی کە شوێنە عەیبەکەم لە دەرەوەیە و ئەوە نیشانەیەیەکی باش نییە. دایکم هەمیشە پێی کوتبووم ئەو شوێنە تەنیا دەبێ من بیبینم و تۆ! جوان فێری کردبووم چۆن ئاگام لێی بێت.. تەنانەت چەندجارێک کە ویستبووم بیخورێنم لێم تووڕە ببوو، پێی کوتبووم دەبێ بە دزی بیخورێنم و نابێ کەس بمبینێ کە دەستی بۆ دەبەم چون "عەیبە"! وە من بە هەستس شەرمی مناڵانە لەوەی کە کەسێکی جیا لە دایکم شوێنە عەیبەکەی منی دیتووە و ترسی پیاوێک کە بە خۆدزینەوەی لە من زانیم تاوانێکی کردووە، خۆم وەک تاوانبار و ئەوەی کە بمهەوێت بیشارمەوە و نەوەکوو کەس بزانێت، بە قەیتانی سەر گیرفانی شەڕواڵەکەم هەوڵم دا هەڵیکێشمەوە سەرێ. 
ئێستا بەڵام کەسێکی تر کە دایکم نەبوو و خۆشم نەبووم زمانی پێداهێنابوو و بە چاو دیتبووی و بە دەست لەمسی کردبوو، بە پەنجەکانی ئەولاولای گرتبوو،.... تەڕ ببووم، تەڕێکی قیزەون.

ئەوە هەموو ئەو شتانە بوو کە لە مێشکم دابوو، ترسێکی ترسناک داگیری کردبووم کە میز دە جێگا کردنی ئەو بەیانی گەواهی بوو. بە جەستەی زەریفی مناڵانەمەوە هەستم دەکرد هێزێک بەقەد قورسایی ئەو میچە قەڵەشیوەی سەر سەرم منی بە ئەرزەکەوە نووساندووە و ناهێڵێت بجووڵێم.☟☟☟☟☟
بۆ_من_ڕووی_داوە_بۆ_تۆ_چی

لە ناوەڕاستی بێستانێک کە تازە بڕکەکانی چەقەرەیان کردبوو، باوکم پێش ئەوەی بخەوین کووتی کە بەیانی زوو هەستین. کاتی بژار و تەنکە هاتووە! من لە کار نەدەترسام. مناڵێکی 6ساڵانی زۆر زیندوو بووم.. ئەوە قسەی دایکمە چون خۆم هیچم لە منداڵیم پێش ئەو شەوە لەبیر نەماوە.
بە جوڵانی شتێکی تەڕ لەسەر جەستەم چاوەکانم پچڕان لە عالەمی خەو. ترپەی دڵم ژوورەکەی کەڕ کرد. جەستەم کارەساتی بەسەر هاتبوو. چاوەکانم دوایین ئەندامی جەستەم بوون کە بە کارەساتی قەوماویان زانی.
ئەوەی من بینیم پیاوێک بوو کە لەسەر ئەژنۆ ڕای کردە ناو جێگاکە، کاتێک کە هەستی کرد چاوم کراوەتەوە. 
بەر چاوی من میچێکی قەڵەشیو بوو کە زۆر حەزم دەکرد بکەوێتە خوارەوە و لەو دڵەکووتەیە، لەو بێدەنگییە، لەو گەرمایە، لەو هەناسانەی تەقەلایان دەکرد بۆ هەوایەکەک کە نەبوو...
گەرمکونە خانەخانەکەی دایکم لە مەلاجامی مەهاباد بۆی کڕیبوومم پێش خەوتن لە پێدا بوو و ئێستا تا سەر ئەژنۆ داکێشرابوو! دەمزانی کە شوێنە عەیبەکەم لە دەرەوەیە و ئەوە نیشانەیەیەکی باش نییە. دایکم هەمیشە پێی کوتبووم ئەو شوێنە تەنیا دەبێ من بیبینم و تۆ! جوان فێری کردبووم چۆن ئاگام لێی بێت.. تەنانەت چەندجارێک کە ویستبووم بیخورێنم لێم تووڕە ببوو، پێی کوتبووم دەبێ بە دزی بیخورێنم و نابێ کەس بمبینێ کە دەستی بۆ دەبەم چون "عەیبە"! وە من بە هەستس شەرمی مناڵانە لەوەی کە کەسێکی جیا لە دایکم شوێنە عەیبەکەی منی دیتووە و ترسی پیاوێک کە بە خۆدزینەوەی لە من زانیم تاوانێکی کردووە، خۆم وەک تاوانبار و ئەوەی کە بمهەوێت بیشارمەوە و نەوەکوو کەس بزانێت، بە قەیتانی سەر گیرفانی شەڕواڵەکەم هەوڵم دا هەڵیکێشمەوە سەرێ. 
ئێستا بەڵام کەسێکی تر کە دایکم نەبوو و خۆشم نەبووم زمانی پێداهێنابوو و بە چاو دیتبووی و بە دەست لەمسی کردبوو، بە پەنجەکانی ئەولاولای گرتبوو،.... تەڕ ببووم، تەڕێکی قیزەون.

ئەوە هەموو ئەو شتانە بوو کە لە مێشکم دابوو، ترسێکی ترسناک داگیری کردبووم کە میز دە جێگا کردنی ئەو بەیانی گەواهی بوو. بە جەستەی زەریفی مناڵانەمەوە هەستم دەکرد هێزێک بەقەد قورسایی ئەو میچە قەڵەشیوەی سەر سەرم منی بە ئەرزەکەوە نووساندووە و ناهێڵێت بجووڵێم.☟☟☟☟☟

text:
o conto| drama | 114 min | 2018
direção e roteiro: jennifer fox
____________________________
sinopse: o conto é uma investigação pessoal da diretora jennifer fox sobre a sua primeira relação sexual. confrontando os cantos mais escondidos de sua memória, jenny tenta entender o que de fato se passou em sua infância e o que era verdade ou correto nos momentos vividos. 
_____________________________
crítica: em 2017, o movimento “#metoo” foi escolhido pela revista time como a “personalidade” do ano, tamanha a sua importância. a hashtag repercutiu ao longo do globo atingindo celebridades que quebraram o silêncio sobre os abusos que sofreram. dentro desse contexto, está a diretora e produtora jennifer fox, interpretada - durante sua fase adulta - por laura dern.
•
o filme traz um retrato sobre as mentiras que contamos a nós mesmos para superarmos um evento traumático. a jenny madura e cineasta confronta a jenny de 13 anos (isabelle nélisse), jovem e ingênua, que queria a todo custo que alguém lhe dissesse que era especial, trazendo, dessa forma, um embate entre as duas personagens - usando, para isso, em determinados momentos, a quebra da 4ª parede. por diversas vezes o filme passa a sensação de estar falando também com seu telespectador, seja quando confronta a vítima perguntando o porquê de ter se enganado e reprimido tudo ou quando fala com o abusador e com as pessoas que sabiam e se calaram.
•
o conto é uma obra difícil de ser assistida, não por não ser excelente, mas por mostrar a perspectiva de uma vítima sobre um abuso real, o filme não é um retrato sensual como em lolita - visto sob os olhos do homem mais velho -, mas um relato de uma agressão que deixou marcas na pessoa que a sofreu. jason ritter, que interpreta bill, tem a dosagem perfeita do charme e perigo contrastados na figura do predador sexual. seu jeito carinhoso e sua forma mansa de falar são a teia para prender jenny e fazer com que ela confie em si cegamente. “vejo que confio tanto nele que nunca entendo onde está me levando. quando já fomos muito longe, nunca sei como dizer não”. o conto é um filme necessário! 
9.8/10

o filme traz um retrato sobre as mentiras que contamos a nós mesmos para superarmos um evento traumático. a jenny madura e cineasta confronta a jenny de 13 anos (isabelle nélisse), jovem e ingênua, que queria a todo custo que alguém lhe dissesse que era especial, trazendo, dessa forma, um embate entre as duas personagens - usando, para isso, em determinados momentos, a quebra da 4ª parede. por diversas vezes o filme passa a sensação de estar falando também com seu telespectador, seja quando confronta a vítima perguntando o porquê de ter se enganado e reprimido tudo ou quando fala com o abusador e com as pessoas que sabiam e se calaram.
•
o conto é uma obra difícil de ser assistida, não por não ser excelente, mas por mostrar a perspectiva de uma vítima sobre um abuso real, o filme não é um retrato sensual como em lolita - visto sob os olhos do homem mais velho -, mas um relato de uma agressão que deixou marcas na pessoa que a sofreu. jason ritter, que interpreta bill, tem a dosagem perfeita do charme e perigo contrastados na figura do predador sexual. seu jeito carinhoso e sua forma mansa de falar são a teia para prender jenny e fazer com que ela confie em si cegamente. “vejo que confio tanto nele que nunca entendo onde está me levando. quando já fomos muito longe, nunca sei como dizer não”. o conto é um filme necessário! 
9.8/10

text:
sad reality of our world... shared from @christycel -  thanks  @warif_ng >>> what happens to a rape survivor  when she seeks help on the streets?
.
.
abaad, a lebanese ngo, conducted a social experiment to see how bystanders would react.

an actress played the role of a rape survivor seeking help in public. these are the real reactions she got.
blaming the survivor is still very prevalent in our society today’, it could have happened anywhere and the reactions would still be the same. 
we need to do better as bystanders so that women and girls can live in a society free from rape and sexual violence.  #shameonwho #endsexualviolence #preventsexualassault #supportingsurvivors #metoo  #sdg5 ....beyound the regular! - #regrann

text:
pernyataan dari seorang feminis muslim berkebangsaan maroko fatima mernissi. bagi kalangan akademisi mungkin tidak asing dengan tokoh ini, mungkin ada yang belum pernah mendengar sama sekali?
.
kalimat yang kami kutip  bertendensi mengandung gugatan dan tersirat unsur pemberontakan,meski jika dikaji secara mendalam memiliki titik benar.
.
masih hangat dengan istilah feminisme. berdasarkan uraian sejarah, feminisme selalu dikaitkan dengan gerakan politis, pemberontakan perempuan yang menuntut hak atas nama diskriminasi, penindasan dan marginalisasi. feminisme lahir berdasarkan konteks sosial masa lalu, munculnya beberapa aliran menyiratkan sebuah penilaian bahwa kajian ini unik. setiap aliran memiliki latar belakang berbeda mulai dari gelombang pertama sampai pada gelombang ketiga meski tujuannya sama menyelesaikan problematika perempuan.

sumber : jurnal dinamika wacana mahasiswa berparadigma vol. 11 th.xxi desember 2015 maret 2016.
kontroversi hermeneutika fatima mernissi : feminisme vs islam puritan.

text:
you are enough. 
you may be too much for some people, those are not your people. 
there isn’t anywhere for you to get, and there’s nothing for you to prove. 
and anyone’s response has nothing to do with you, and everything to do with them. 
baby steps.  and everyday just a little bit more and a little bit better. 
be easy on yourself, lots of deep breaths. 
we got this.

i'll be presenting a workshop today at 4pm called "got consent?", centered around facilitating discussions about consent with young people using text. come through if you're uptown!

.

#repost @mosaicmagazine
・・・
november 17, 12pm • the bronx museum 
1040 grand concourse, bronx, ny 
free event • workshops • panels • film • #mlc2018
keynote: nicole dennis-benn, writer/activist

the mlc2018 is a grassroots event and a great opportunity for the bronx and new york city communities of educators, students, program administrators, and parents to learn ways to integrate books and reading into the lives of teenagers. mlc offers a mix of informative programs and creative workshops to engage young minds, strengthen literacy, and develop education strategies.

130-230pm
#metoo & the movement
black women writers conjuring in the continuum 
in 2017, the #metoo campaign amplified the voices of survivors of rape, sexual assault and harassment. though social media platforms became the route to shared survivor stories, creating heightened awareness, accountability, and solidarity in response to a pervasive rape culture that is generations-deep, black women writers have courageously confronted patriarchal violence on the page while simultaneously experiencing a spectrum of abuses and violations in our personal lives. this panel, inspired by the break beat poets’ black girl magic anthology, as well as other creative collaborations and alliances, will continue this urgently important conversation. through this community dialogue,we will explore the continuum of black women writing against all that would attempt to violate our lives. we will elevate our stories, our activism, our labor, and lineage. 
panelists: jp howard, keisha-gaye anderson, and diamond sharp. facilitator: nina angela mercer
name: T. L. Daniels

“उमर भर ग़ालिब यही भूल करता रहा
धूल चहेरे पे थी और आइना साफ करता रहा.!!” @akashgalgate’s short film is an answer to how a man takes, a ‘walk of pride’ in the society when he comes out of a woman’s world. which shouldn't be right for neither of the cases but when a woman comes out of a man’s world, that’s a ‘walk of shame’. it's almost as if she is straight out of a terrorist attack/horror movie.

nonetheless, society is taken forward by information and ideas that are accepted collectively. that is why this is not a ‘film’ but a ‘mirror’ itself, a mirror where maybe society could see its face someday. hopefully!

press release
keep rising to the top presents
“east side story, peace in the east”
29th anniversary 2018 event 
new york--- kr3t’s choreographer violeta galagarza host a celebration for their 29th anniversary called “the east side story, peace in the east”

aaron davis hall, marian anderson theater, 115 convent ave, new york, ny 10027.  in the past, life struggles taught us how to be content and grateful for the little we had.  people now have more clothes, digital gadgets and shoes than they did growing up, but they’re still not happy; and never satisfied.
this show looks at what results from compromising family values for material wealth and how it’s destroying our communities.  we will shine light on the #metoo movement, all the violence in the community and dance tribute for junior who was brutally murdered in the bronx, our goal is to send a positive message to everyone through the art of dance.
 in addition we are glad to have our event hosted by jason andors & imagine, who have appeared on hbo’s bad boys of comedy, comedy central’s premium blend, showtime at the apollo and bet’s comic view.  music by legendary re-mix dj ted smooth.
 five kr3t’s established choreographers will be presenting dance numbers. several have performed on world tours with artists such as j-lo, chris brown, rihanna, beyoncé, lady gaga, usher, kelly rowland, missy elliot, as well on tv shows like the grammy's the vma's jimmy fallon and much more.
our goal is to provide an outlet to develop dance and life skills that will enhance their lifestyles long term. 
no matter what the obstacles, our dancers
keep rising to the top #ripjunior @junior_mami_ingodbelieve thank you @renaissance.ny  for the shirts and @dezzysfootwear 💋💯❤ great puece by @francoth3artist

text:
[21年前照#metoo]

現年29歲的金融界女高層，聽聞有女運動員公開多年前的性侵經歷，受到啟發 ，向警方舉報比她年長7至8歲的表哥，指控表哥於21年前非禮她超過30次。表哥早前被裁定3項非禮罪成。 
裁判官今指本案事發多年，被告犯案時只得14歲，這是重要的考慮判刑因素；而非禮雖是嚴重罪行，但本案情節遠較其他案例輕微，故決定輕判被告接受感化一年，並寄語被告與女事主均要重新振作，勇敢面對將來的挑戰。 
本案男被告案發時14歲，女事主x則年約8至9歲。其中兩次案發時，被告藉詞搔癢，觸及x乳頭；另有一次被告抱起x，手部觸摸x私處。 
裁判官判刑時指出，從聆訊中得悉女事主x與被告兩家人關係密切，無論過時過節抑或被告結婚等重要日子，兩家人均一起渡過。x亦承認在升學及求職問題上也有求教於被告，顯示多年來雙方關係良好，被告於適當時亦會向她提供協助。 
感化官報告則指，現年36歲的被告學有所成，在金融界闖出事業，並已結婚及育有小孩。感化官認為被告有悔意，建議感化12個月。至於x的創傷評估報告則顯示她事後心理受影響，患上抑鬱。

#女權 #feminism #fight #for #world #peace #and #gender #equality #forever #feminist

text:
i am excited to pre-release a single ‘feels like freedom’ from my upcoming ep. i hope you’ll check it out in the link below. i wrote this song because i had to. 
my first ‘me too’ experience happened when i was just 15 years old. i shut down. i trampled my own voice, and my own feelings, as far down as i could. embracing emptiness felt like an escape from everything pushed down below. years later, coming back to myself, i realized that kind of escape only built another kind of prison. writing songs has become a big part of the alchemy of rediscovering my own voice. this song is dedicated to those of us- and the parts of ourselves- whose pain goes unspoken, yet longs to cry out: may we all be heard. 
lyric video here:
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=eauq_eol-q4&feature=youtu.be

text:
dneska děkuju za krásný den. oslavili jsme s celou rodinou moje, táty, dědy, babičky... všechny narozeniny, které se za tu dlouhou dobu nastřádaly. tyhle prskavky byly na dortu od mamky, kterej byl prosimvás nejen zdravej, ale taky dobrej!! takže tohle srdce není jen pro ty co se mnou slaví narozeniny, ale pro ty co uz je měli nebo mít budou a hlavně pro všechny co slaví toho 17. listopadu.
doufám, že všichni ví o co jde. podle mě je to tak důležité , hlavně pro nás děcka. je jen na nás jak s tou svobodou naložíme!! stejně jako o životní prostředí, sociální sítě, módu, zdravou výživu, kampaň #metoo ...bychom se měli zajímat právě naší budoucností v tom politickém pojetí.
takže tohle je pro všechny, co cokoliv a jakkoliv slaví!
tak krásný sobotní sváteční večer🖤🖤🥂v.

text:
functional movement + yoga for recovery! 
bits & pieces of @erikasagekelley‘s recovery plan in action... goal is to build flexibility and gently get back into a workout regimen. 
when recovering from an injury or newly recovered, don’t feel pressured to hop right back into your “normal” routine. this could prove to do more harm than good to your body and your ego. 
instead incorporate functional moves and some yoga. they both strengthen and condition the body to return to “status quo”. remember it will take time and be patient with the process. ✌🏾 @erikasagekelley

meet the victims of your "choices"... milk, cheese, ice cream, etc.
_
repost from @sosanimalscall  @theoccultussoulband
_
the dairy industry heavy marketed themselves for profit, such as the “got milk?” commercials.
.
“got milk” was actually an advertising campaign to encourage the consumption of milk, created by an advertising agency for the california milk processor board in 1993, and was later licensed for use by milk processors and dairy farmers.
.
the truth was hidden from us. and over time those who profited from exploiting animals, conditioned us.
.
maybe we were victims of the dairy industry ourselves, but we can no longer be complicit.
.
be #strong enough to seek the #truth, because the truth is out there. it will be through your own eyes, your own truth, in which you will find your own way to break out of that mold.
.

text:
@regran_ed from @elishaattai -  as we prepare for awlo 2018 induction and fundraising dinner, please permit me to share a few lines about this global women movement.

african women in leadership organisation (awlo), is for female leaders of african descent, entrepreneurs, professionals, civic leaders - to empower them to be high impact leaders.
we are creating a platform that is empowering and inclusive, for female leaders to sour and
by association garner leadership experience.

our key actions are:

leadership development

we have realized that women leaders must be in a continual process of leadership development to attain their full potential. we provide experiential leadership development opportunities for women.

impact

we believe that making impact is proof of leadership effectiveness. we are sold out to service and also provide opportunities for women leaders to take action or participate in global development.

connecting women

one of our most effective tools for women leadership development has been networking. we provide women opportunities to connect, and develop profitable relationships. our chapters' support-system-framework has been a potent model for this.

for awlo membership registration please  click on this link www.awlo.org/membership

i specially welcome you great women of worth from across the world and all the distinguished #heforshe men to this amazing movement.

website: www.awlo.org

we are not an event but a movement.

thank you! - #regrann

text:
“does the evidence out-rule the possibility that she was attracted to the defendant and was open to meeting someone and being with someone? you have to look at the way she was dressed. she was wearing a thong with a lace front.”
---
in ireland, defense lawyer used a teenage girl's thong as evidence in a rape trial to suggest the girl consented to sex. the man accused was acquitted and declared not guilty after. this is unacceptable. a person's underwear does not equal consent to sex. i stand by the girl and demand change for justice systems so rape victims would not have to be scared of reporting in the first place.
#thisisnotconsent

text:
잃을게 없어서, 꾸미기가 귀찮아서 머리를 자른 것도 아니다. 아는 사람을 마주하는건 솔직히 아직 불편하고 낯설다. 그리고 나를 이상하게 보는 시선이 두렵지 않다면 거짓말이다.
.
머리를 짧게 자른 나를 봤을 때, 나는 잘어울리지도, 멋있지도 않았다. 솔직히 내 헤어 스타일은 맹구같고 쥐 파먹은 느낌이었다. 그렇지만 숏컷이 잘 어울리는 사람이 되고자 하는 순간, '미소년같은 여성' 이라는 또다른 코르셋을 다시 쓰게 될까봐 늘 그런 생각을 견제하고 있다.
.
코르셋을 하나둘씩 벗어나가는 동안, 나의 삶은 너무 자유로워졌고, 편리해졌다. 평소 나는 샤워부터 외출 준비까지 1시간정도 걸리는 사람이었다. 중요한 약속이 있을때는 화장을 하다가 지각을 한 적도 꽤 있었다. 누군가는 나를 책임감이 없는 사람으로 바라봤겠지만 나는 화장을 안해서 제 시간에 도착하는 것보다, 지각을 하더라도 화장을 하고 가는 것이 차라리 더  예의있고 책임감 있는 것이라 생각했었다. 그렇지만 이젠 샤워하고 옷 입기까지 5분이면 된다. 매일 꼬박꼬박 하던 트리트먼트와 린스, 헤어 에센스는 이제 필요없다. 그냥 수건으로 물기를 털어 버리면 그만이다. 대신 남는 55분은 평생 먹지도 못해본 아침 밥을 챙겨 먹고, 책을 읽게 되었다. 스스로가 생산적인 행동을 하며 인생을 다시 설계하고있다.
.
우리 엄마는 화장대도 없고, 원래 화장을 하지 않는 사람이었고, 우리 자매는 그런 엄마의 영향을 많이 받아왔다. 동생은 아예 화장을 하지않아 화장품이 없고, 나 또한 가끔 화장을 했을 뿐이었다. 평소에 자주 꾸미지 않던 우리자매도 [남자의 모습을 하고 있는게 이렇게 편하고 효율적인지 모르고 살았다는게 억울해서, 고등학생때로 돌아가고 싶다] 고 이야기한다.
.
페미니스트인 나를 걱정하고 응원하는 많은 친구들이 있다. 나를 아끼고 생각해주는 마음은 정말 고맙다. 그렇지만 그런 걱정과 응원은 자신의 상황과 나의 상황을 다른 것이라 정의하고 구분짓고 있는 것으로 느껴져 가끔은 그런 응원과 걱정에 슬퍼진다.
.
성차별과 가부장제, 성적대상화의 여성혐오는 나, 은수 만의 일이 아니다. 우리 모두의 일이다. 특별한 사건이 아니다. 우리의 삶 곳곳에 촘촘하게 녹아있는 일상이다. 요즘에만 유행하는 트렌드가 아니다. 조선시대에도 있어왔다. 나는 내 주위에 있는 소중한 사람들이 언젠가 나에 대한 응원과 걱정을 넘어서, 이런 차별과 혐오에 맞서줄 거라 믿고 싶다. 물론 그들에게 강요하지도, 조급해 하지도 않을 것이다. 여성들은 언젠가 조금씩, 느리겠지만 앞으로 나아갈 것이라 믿기 때문이다.
.
요즘 나는 자유민주주의의 2018년에 살고있는 나를 되돌아보며, 늘 먼저 앞장서서 사회의 방향을 바로잡기 위해 용기를 내어 모든 것을 희생했던 많은 분들께 부채의식을 느끼고 있다. 그리고 그 결정을 실천으로 옮기기까지 얼마나 많은 어려움이 있었을지 미약하게나마 이해하게 된 것도 같다. 앞으로의 나는, 누군가 내게 용기를 주었던 것 처럼, 나도 누군가의 용기가 되기 위해 안주하지 않고 노력할 것이다. 아직 용기내지 못한 누군가에게 이 글이 작게나마 용기가 되길 바란다.
name: 박은수 EunSoo Park 朴恩秀

stop_filter_tweet: 잃을게 없어서 , 꾸미기가 귀찮아서 머리를 자른 것도 아니다 . 아는 사람을 마주하는건 솔직히 아직 불편하고 낯설다 . 그리고 나를 이상하게 보는 시선이 두렵지 않다면 거짓말이다 . . 머리를 짧게 자른 나를 봤을 때 , 나는 잘어울리지도 , 멋있지도 않았다 . 솔직히 내 헤어 스타일은 맹구같고 쥐 파먹은 느낌이었다 . 그렇지만 숏컷이 잘 어울리는 사람이 되고자 하는 순간 , '미소년같은 여성 ' 이라는 또다른 코르셋을 다시 쓰게 될까봐 늘 그런 생각을 견제하고 있다 . . 코르셋을 하나둘씩 벗어나가는 동안 , 나의 삶은 너무 자유로워졌고 , 편리해졌다 . 평소 나는 샤워부터 외출 준비까지 1시간정도 걸리는 사람이었다 . 중요한 약속이 있을때는 화장을 하다가 지각을 한 적도 꽤 있었다 . 누군가는 나를 책임감이 없는 사람으로 바라봤겠지만 나는 화장을 안해서 제 시간에 도착하는 것보다 , 지각을 하더라도 화장을 하고 가는 것이 차라리 더 예의있고 책임감 있는 것이라 생각했었다 . 그렇지만 이젠 샤워하고 옷 입기까지 5분이면 된다 . 매일 꼬박꼬박 하던 트리트먼트와 린스 , 헤어 에센스는 이제 필요없다 . 그냥 수건으로 물기를 털어 버리면 그만이다 . 대신 남는 55분은 평생 먹지도 못해본 아침 밥을 챙겨 먹고 , 책을 읽게 되었다 . 스스로가 생산적인 행동을 하며 인생을 다시 설계하고있다 . . 우리 엄마는 화장대도 없고 , 원래 화장을 하지 않는 사람이었고 , 우리 자매는 그런 엄마의 영향을 많이 받아왔다 . 동생은 아예 화장을 하지않아 화장품이 없고 , 나 또한 가끔 화장을 했을 뿐이었다 . 평소에 자주 꾸미지 않던 우리자매도 [ 남자의 모습을 하고 있는게 이렇게 편하고 효율적인지 모르고 살았다는게 억울해서 , 고등학생때로 돌아가고 싶다 ] 고 이야기한다 . . 페미니스트인 나를 걱정하고 응원하는 많은 친구들이 있다 . 나를 아끼고 생각해주는 마음은 정말 고맙다 . 그렇지만 그런 걱정과 응원은 자신의 상황과 나의 상황을 다른 것이라 정의하고 구분짓고 있는 것으로 느껴져 가끔은 그런 응원과 걱정에 슬퍼진다 . . 성차별과 가부장제 , 성적대상화의 여성혐오는 나 , 은수 만의 일이 아니다 . 우리 모두의 일이다 . 특별한 사건이 아니다 . 우리의 삶 곳곳에 촘촘하게 녹아있는 일상이다 . 요즘에만 유행하는 트렌드가 아니다 . 조선시대에도 있어왔다 . 나는 내 주위에 있는 소중한 사람들이 언젠가 나에 대한 응원과 걱정을 넘어서 , 이런 차별과 혐오에 맞서줄 거라 믿고 싶다 . 물론 그들에게 강요하지도 , 조급해 하지도 않을 것이다 . 여성들은 언젠가 조금씩 , 느리겠지만 앞으로 나아갈 것이라 믿기 때문이다 . . 요즘 나는 자유민주주의의 2018년에 살고있는 나를 되돌아보며 , 늘 먼저 앞장서서 사회의 방향을 바로잡기 위해 용기를 내어 모든 것을 희생했던 많은 분들께 부채의식을 느끼고 있다 . 그리고 그 결정을 실천으로 옮기기까지 얼마나 많은 어려움이 있었을지 미약하게나마 이해하게 된 것도 같다 . 앞으로의 나는 , 누군가 내게 용기를 주었던 것 처럼 , 나도 누군가의 용기가 되기 위해 안주하지 않고 노력할 것이다 . 아직 용기내지 못한 누군가에게 이 글이 작게나마 용기가 되길 바란다 .

new york--- kr3t’s,  choreographers host a celebration for their 29th anniversary called “the east side story, peace in the east”

in the past, life struggles taught us how to be content and grateful for the little we had.  people now have more clothes, digital gadgets and shoes than they did growing up, but they’re still not happy; and never satisfied.
this show looks at what results from compromising family values for material wealth and how it’s destroying our communities.  we will shine light on the #metoo movement, all the violence in the community and dance tribute for junior who was brutally murdered in the bronx, our goal is to send a positive message to everyone through the art of dance.
 in addition we are glad to have our event hosted by jason andors & imagine, who have appeared on hbo’s bad boys of comedy, comedy central’s premium blend, showtime at the apollo and bet’s comic view.  music by legendary re-mix dj ted smooth.
 five kr3t’s established choreographers will be presenting dance numbers. several have performed on world tours with artists such as j-lo, chris brown, rihanna, beyoncé, lady gaga, usher, kelly rowland, missy elliot, as well on tv shows like the grammy's the vma's jimmy fallon and much more.
our goal is to provide an outlet to develop dance and life skills that will enhance their lifestyles long term. 
no matter what the obstacles, our dancers
keep rising to the top

new york--- kr3t’s,  choreographers host a celebration for their 29th anniversary called “the east side story, peace in the east”

in the past, life struggles taught us how to be content and grateful for the little we had.  people now have more clothes, digital gadgets and shoes than they did growing up, but they’re still not happy; and never satisfied.
this show looks at what results from compromising family values for material wealth and how it’s destroying our communities.  we will shine light on the  movement, all the violence in the community and dance tribute for junior who was brutally murdered in the bronx, our goal is to send a positive message to everyone through the a of dance.
 in addition we are glad to have our event hosted by jason andors & imagine, who have appeared on hbo’s bad boys of comedy, comedy central’s premium blend, showtime at the apollo and bet’s comic view.  music by legendary re-mix dj ted smooth.
 five kr3t’s established choreographers will be presenting dance numbers. several have performed on world tours with aists such as j-lo, chris brown, rihanna, beyoncé, lady gaga, usher, kelly rowland, missy elliot, as well on tv shows like the grammy's the vma's jimmy fallon and much more.
our goal is to provide an outlet to develop dance and life skills that will enhance their lifestyles long term.

text:
best perk of participating in film festivals is getting to meet amazing poeple and forming new connections. met these kickass women  at @regentparkfilm today. @tendisaic, azeezah kanji good to see you! @aniquejordan i feel so much more informed & energized after sharing space with you on today's digital activism panel. thanks a lot again to all the women who feature in my short #wesayknow. #wesayknow is a short video that i made amidst protests against 2015 updates to #sexed in ontario. it amplifies muslim women's voice on need for sexual health education. i am glad to have screened it at #rpff18 today as with the repeal of the curriculum it seems even more timely. huge shout out to the entire rpff team for all the work they have put into organizing this festival.

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
for those who are doubting me and my story, i am not here to change your minds. 
i have shared my experience with the hopes of encouraging other women and girls to do the same; to help uplift and let other women know that they don’t have to suffer in silence; and to challenge some of the debilitating beliefs, mentality and attitudes in our community and society that discourages others to speak out and fight for what is right. .
.
and finally i want to address why i did not name him: - it’s not relevant who it was. the point was that it happened;
- i didn’t want to go into the trouble of legalities when it comes to printing his name; - i meant what i said when i said that i forgive him. forgiveness means a chance to start anew;
- i didn’t want to make the story about him or me; rather i want to focus on advocating for women and women who has gone through sexual assault and/or violence. i just shared the story as enough as i can to form the basis for my advocacy.

now, i hope that you can support this cause because it’s been a very difficult and painful journey. even more difficult now that i am speaking about it. while i have many detractors (just as i have many supporters); i won’t let them silence or re-victimize me again. 
remember, this is for us. #filipinasspeakout #metoo 
thank you.

text:
an expansion on yesterdays story.
.
.
yesterday, i wore a skirt. went downtown to meet my husband and had a complete stranger grab my ass under my skirt. he did not look like a creep. just like a regular white guy in his late thirties. there are two ways this situation could have gone:
.
1⃣ i could have stayed quiet and complacent and accepted the fact that i am a woman wearing a skirt and therefore i may get my ass unwilling grabbed. *insert sarcasm and eye rolling*

2⃣ use that great cross that @nicdmuay and @buckleyjiujitsu have been teaching me, and box that douche square in the nose on a crowded train and then fill out a full report with security so they can find him and penalize him for sexually harrassing a woman who did nothing more than wear a skirt in public. .
.
i can fucking tell you now, option one was never really an option. so many women have recently spoken out about unwanted sexual advances and so the one incident in my life that i could have ever felt like a victim, i sure as hell didn't. yes, i felt wronged and angry af, but never victimized. and the reason i didn't feel victimized is because he left way worse than i did. he left clutching a bleeding nose and cursing, i left, filled out my report and carried on with my evening, still wearing my short skirt. 👗 (though my husband and my daddy both told me i should have hit him again so that he couldn't have so casually walked away into a crowd of people.) .
.
so please, if you worry about your safety or your loved ones, learn to defend yourself, make sure your loved ones can too, and don't be victimized. the discussion i had with my daughter this morning summed up in "if someone touches you without your permission, beat them until they stop and make sure you have the skills to do that."
.
.
cheers to all the women taking self defense classes, cheers to the men and women teaching them, and here's to the asshole with the bloody nose that let me give a first hand example to my daughter on how to handle douchebags on trains.

yesterday, i wore a ski. went downtown to meet my husband and had a complete stranger grab my ass under my ski. he did not look like a creep. just like a regular white guy in his late thiies. there are two ways this situation could have gone:
.
1⃣ i could have stayed quiet and complacent and accepted the fact that i am a woman wearing a ski and therefore i may get my ass unwilling grabbed. *inse sarcasm and eye rolling*

2⃣ use that great cross that  and  have been teaching me, and box that douche square in the nose on a crowded train and then fill out a full repo with security so they can find him and penalize him for sexually harrassing a woman who did nothing more than wear a ski in public. .
.
i can fucking tell you now, option one was never really an option. so many women have recently spoken out about unwanted sexual advances and so the one incident in my life that i could have ever felt like a victim, i sure as hell didn't. yes, i felt wronged and angry af, but never victimized. and the reason i didn't feel victimized is because he left way worse than i did. he left clutching a bleeding nose and cursing, i left, filled out my repo and carried on with my evening, still wearing my sho ski. 👗 (though my husband and my daddy both told me i should have hit him again so that he couldn't have so casually walked away into a crowd of people.) .
.
so please, if you worry about your safety or your loved ones, learn to defend yourself, make sure your loved ones can too, and do not be victimized. the discussion i had with my daughter this morning summed up in "if someone touches you without your permission, beat them until they stop and make sure you have the skills to do that."
.
.
cheers to all the women taking self defense classes, cheers to the men and women teaching them, and here's to the asshole with the bloody nose that let me give a first hand example to my daughter on how to handle douchebags on trains.

text:
has #metoo prompted you to rethink the roles you choose?
"you always have to look at the impact a part is going to have and how a part is handled. we had an interesting conversation about this on “the nest” [a forthcoming psychodrama about a businessman and his family] because of the way my character and others around him treated the women in the office. it was set in 1986, and people were discussing, “do we slap them on the ass or use derogatory terms?” and i was like, “wait a minute, we’re not in the ’80s. we’re making this film now. so yeah, you can include that if you make a point in saying, ‘we were wrong.’ but if you’re not, then there’s no point in just continuing the myth.” jude law for the new york times💭📸 #judelaw #actor #newyorktimes #interview #thenest #movie #80s

text:
when i was 17 years old, i was out, it was late. a man much older than me, much stronger than me, grabbed me and started dragging me into the alleyway, he called me a filthy bitch and he smiled. my best friend tried her best to get him away from me as i told him to get off, he then turned on her and started to strangle her. i've never, ever forgotten how pertrifying it felt, thank god we were saved by some other guys.
i was wearing a thong that night.... i wasn't giving consent.

how could you? how could you do this? how dare you imply how we choose to dress means we're asking to be raped. every hour roughly 11 men and women are raped in the united kingdom... just let that settle in for a minute. because that means in the next 30 minutes at least 5 people will be scarred for life, permanently damaged at the hands of rapists. those rapists can be acquitted, because of the minor detail of what we consider consent??? that's not okay, that's disgusting. it's a fucking disgrace and there will be men and women who won't come forward because they'll believe there isn't a point, because they feel ashamed, they'll feel dirty and they'll believe we won't do anything about it, that we'll judge because of the underwear they wore, the place they hung around in and the fact "her dress was a bit slutty". it must stop, because i see the mental turmoil rape leaves victims, it's something that goes with them to their grave and they often feel petrified to admit it over fear of judgement. 
stand by my side, hold my hand and shout it until they can't take it anymore, until they listen and they understand this is not consent. 
i do believe if we say it loud enough, we won't just make waves, we'll change lives, we'll effectively support victims and instead of leaving them to fester with their own self loathing and belief they're totally alone, we'll instead take their hand and say #metoo and heal together.

#thisisnotconsent
#stoprapeshaming 
#support 
#encourage 
#underwearisnotconsent 
#standstrong
#shoutuntiltheyunderstand

text:
be with someone who will cater to your soul, someone who will be there for you when you feel vulnerable and weak. 
be with someone who will see your needs and make attempts to meet them, someone who wont curse and criticize you, especially when you are down. 
be with someone who isn't selfish and can support you without feeling inadequate or jealous of your accomplishments.  be with someone who will make attempts to understand you beyond the words you speak. 
be with someone who will not cheapen your worth by entertaining everyone else and disregarding your relationship!

text:
why are we pretending we don’t know what consent and assault is. it’s been happening since forever, but now because women are gaining rights and have a voice, some men who think women gaining rights, is taking away theirs, they say stuff like ‘i can’t even talk to a woman anymore’, ‘why did she come out about it from years ago, we’re not safe’. to some the #metoo was a shock, but for many it’s been a reality for too long. this is real. you can talk to a woman, you can compliment her, but you can’t shout degrading comments from a car window. why are we making it seem like it’s so hard to not sexually assault someone, ‘rip the good old days’. it’s disgusting. clothes are not consent, clothes also don’t cause rape. let’s put the blame where it belongs, with the perpetrator. no means no. but so does uncomfortable laughter, flinching, moving away, silence, unconscious. it alway was, don’t be scared unless you have sexually assaulted anyone. times up, for those patriarchal predators. ~beyoncé 🌼
#thisisnotconsent #rape #sexualassault #nomeansno #consent #victimblaming #feminist #activism #socialjustice #ireland #change #weneedtochange

text:
european champion!
naga, middleweight, adult, expert

text:
as a man who cares about equality, the true meaning of the word feminist is one i want to understand more.
-
just last weekend, my mum told me she first stood up for equality when she was 13 years old. a teacher at school said “can two strong boys help me out 💪” to which my mum rightly and bravely challenged him (she did the helping!)
-
it sparked a realisation in me, that i can’t possibly know what it’s like to be a women. but it feels really important to make an effort to ask more questions to loved ones and read books like this.
-
i hope as men and women continue to de-stereotype traits and seek to treat each other with complete respect, we’ll live in a happier world.
-
a little effort to understand what women have had to overcome in history 🙌🙏💪
-
i’ll let you know what it’s like.

text: in other news, america should impeach the incredibly abusive sherbert. secondly, disgusted how many priveledged white kids look up to that, following through with their only purpose being to seperate harder working families or new members. that is what the lives of so many ive met here consists of, your actions are worse than anything i've ever done in my life, and guess who gets to experience all the pain, and hate you so freely disperse...me and others from the same background. i literally hang out by myself, to dodge the abusive packs running around...and always have. it's better too. also you're all stupid hanging out in crowds; the amount of violence in this country. so america, why does he do that? why do you let him? i don't let people abuse me, they just do, and i don't respect them at all for it. maybe that's what their parents are so proud of them for, maybe that's why their parents fund them well into their 30s, unlike any reasonable community. is that what they taught you? is that who you were raised to be? honestly, i didn't have people watching me, so maybe that's why i'm nice, still entirely into redirecting the hate i've been given back to the source it appeared from though. it's not attractive. the only reason you have those friends is due to your parents having money. the only reason i know my friends is because we've had to look out for eachother, and i'm proud to know them, we'd never treat others less than human, because we were born into no right. and will continue to proudly survive without that i suppose. #freepress #metoo #blacklivesmatter #waterprotectors #impeach

text:
this song and music video are the result of a huge collaboration of some amazing industry professionals and beautiful creative minds.
together with the help of these incredible individuals, we aim to raise awareness and connect victims with support systems and rehabilitation services. as well as send the very positive message; that there is a life after abuse.
the time is now to stand up and make a real change.
i ask that you all share this project on, so that those who are in need may see it and find the courage to seek help.

text:
this was the mantra in our house with my daughter's growing up. it is something i deeply believe in. in my path of growth, particularly the past three years, this has kept me going. i strive for grace, peace and the strength to make those right choices. while lashing out and hurting people may, in the instant moment, feel good. ultimately it's a stain upon us. when making a right choice, a positive choice it will give a longer lasting satisfaction. it will give you peace. at the end of the day, it is yourself you have to face each day. when you are judged in the afterlife it is your actions you are judged by. do not let the toxicity win.
.

know that you are not along in your journey and your faith in god will see you through whatever storm may come your way.

remember you have the strength and courage inside of you to rise above the challenge and excel in life because you are forever fat.  a true fighter, achiever, & thriver.  a child of god indeed.

text:
a lot of people focus on forgiveness. i choose not to forgive. why should someone be forgiven? 6 years ago today, which happened also to fall on a sunday, we lost our home, hannah had to move from her school, we had to leave town, i moved away from job opportunities,  we lost most of our possessions and nearly lost our lives. since then life has been full of uncertainty and i've taken one hit after another. i don't have to forgive. it will not make moving on easier and seems totally dismissive. my family is not the same. probably never will be. so for everyone else, you do not have to forgive. you can have your feelings. they are valid. 
#violenceagainstwomen #homeinvasion #maleviolence #sexualviolence #nomore #metoo #yesallwomen

text: great time with some great people. another @azlrprs monthly match wrapped up. position heavy match today with the farthest target around 600. definately learned alot from today on getting back to the basics of good fundamentals and slowing down to rebuild a position if what i'm using isn't working. all in all great day outside with good people and learned what i can do to improve... @bighorn_arms #originaction worked flawless the whole day and was butter smooth, @xlrindustries #envychassis was great as always (need to get a full arca version in the future), @leupoldoptics #mark5hd was crystal clear and made seeing shot up targets very easy, @timney_triggers #calvinelite trigger breaking crisp at 8oz when i wanted it to, and the @area419official #hellfire keeping the muzzle under control and keeping my rifle on target under recoil. just need to do my part better in the future. @nationalrifleleague @altamaboots #xlrfamily #timneytribe #leupoldcore #precisionrifle #boltgun #getoutandshoot #runyourboltnotyourmouth #sunnyday #metoo #letfreedomring #sunsoutgunsout #longrangeshooting #65creedmoor #sendit

text:
i received the most profound encouragement from god through the voice of the young warrior i had not yet met. 
all of my prophetic art is divinely guided and inspired by god. most times god is giving me not only the exact image to paint but his words to accompany it.  it’s a very vulnerable feeling to share the words and images with the world.  unlike my other art, there are always the religious proud that challenge me with certain images.  there are hecklers rolling their eyes at the prophecy that’s given. 
one of the pieces titled warrior has touched the hearts of many women. i’m blessed when i hear from them learning of the encouragement it has brought them. 
a few days ago i was literally brought to my knees in tears when the grandmother, meme,  of a very special  young warrior reached out to me.  she had purchased a warrior mug for her granddaughter. what began to unfold has brought me the deepest of encouragement. 
her name is kara johnson.  kara is a thriving survivor of horrific abuse at the hands of her trusted doctor as a young girl.  she led the way as many came forward.  i researched and literally wept learning the details and watching that fierce and brave young warrior fearlessness face larry nassar and not only hold him accountable but boldly proclaim her love of god at his sentencing.  the words she spoke and the path she’s now on mimic with perfection the message that god gave me several years ago. then they sent me her picture from a glamour magazine interview.... my god. 
god is so very, very near all of us.  kara has shared with me the joy and encouragement it has given her.  it has blessed me absolutely profoundly. 
i pray every person that reads this takes a moment to bless kara in the comments below.  her future is intensely bright and filled with so much joy and love.  i can’t wait to meet her personally and hug our beautiful warrior kara.#warrior #beauty #beautyforashes #god #jesus #prophecy #joy #healing #blessed #metoo #soulhealing

text:
when people talk about how easy mental health can be if you just talk it out and take your meds i want to punch them. this is the last year and a half of my meds i have taken, been changed on and off and levels messed with. i had an amazing doctor who went through every play in the book. i became a test subject only to find that no pill is ever going to fix me. i have to fix myself and want to be cured. the struggle to live and die is a daily one and i never feel worthy of time or care. i mostly feel like a burden to my friends. i have a saying that i am less than trash..because trash symbolizes you had something of plenty to throw away. you will never know what is hidden behind a smile and laugh until you see past it into the true dark center of self. 
#meds #medication #depression #anxiety #ocd #borderline #personalitydisorder #pills #mental #health #suicideawareness #notalone #metoo #brokenmind #onepillmakesyoulargerandonepillmakesyousmall #motherslittlehelpers #endos #eatingdisorder #selfabuse #cutter #fasting #wellness #alive

text_retweet:
💖 5 mile hill run 🏃🏼‍♀️💖 so i woke up at 6am to start getting ready for work. as i’m drinking my coffee i open up the newspaper aka instagram. first post is @kurts_runningfitness and he slammed out 10 miles before my alarm even went off. i immediately comment complimenting his run and adding there is no way i will have time to squeeze a run in today. as soon as i posted that comment i thought- come on allison- that’s bullshit. make the time. i had a full day at the salon and then was coming straight home for my 6 year olds birthday party. while listening to my clients talk about themselves i was thinking ... hmmm how can i get in some fitness time???!! ... yes that’s right- your hairstylist isn’t always listening to your drama 😂🤣😂🤣 blocking you out sometimes is a survival tool!!! so i thought - even if i end up running at 9pm it’s going to happen! ❤️”make moves or make excuses”❤️ so i squeezed this in before the party 🎈 🎊 🎂 and a special thanks to kurt (@kurts_runningfitness )you inspired this run to happen. way to slay 🖤  #oymambassador #hairstylist  #inkedgirl #explantista #marathoner #procompressionambassador #runnersrepost  #poweryourpassion  #noexcuses #runspiration #strength #runnerscommunity #motherrunner #getafterit #girlswholift 
#metoo #nogivingup #cosmogirl  #womensrunningcommunity #powerup #strongwomen #dontcompare #empower #inspiringwomenrunners

احتمالا موفق ترین کمپین #تبلیغاتی سال ۲۰۱۸ ،کمپین #دختر_نترس بوده است.
کمپینی که موفقیتی نبوده که  از لحاظ به دست آوردن شاخص های سنجش اثربخشی #تبلیغات به دست نیاورده باشد و این چیزی است که از نگاه داوران #فستیوال های مختلف دور نمانده.
یک بیلیون بازدید #توئیتر ی در عرض ۱۲ ساعت، سه میلیارد و نیم بازدید توئیتری در عرض ۵ هفته، ۴۰۵ میلیون بازدید #اینستاگرامی در شش هفته و دختر نترس در ۱۲۸ کشور دیده شد.
 شبِ #روز_زن سال گذشته بدون اجازه این #مجسمه در برابر مجسمه قدیمی گاو پولساز خیابان #وال_استریت در نیویورک نصب شد و هیاهو و موج خبری بزرگی رو ایجاد کرد.
مجسمه ای که توانست سوار بر موج سنگین کمپین #metoo  شود و نگاه تمام رسانه ها را به خود اختصاص دهد. 
دختر بچه ای که نماد آینده زنان آمریکایی است و با سری بالا در برابر گاو خشمگین وال استریت که نماد جامعه ای مردسالار است می ایستد.
.

#تبلیغات
#کمپین
#برند
#برندینگ
#نیویورک
#shemakesadifference 
#fearless 
#fearlessgirl

text:
happy feminist saturday all, who’s spending it reading? 
a room of one’s own is considered virginia woolf’s most powerful feminist essay, justifying the need for women to possess intellectual freedom and financial independence. based on a lecture given at girton college, cambridge, the essay is one of the great feminist polemics, ranging in its themes from jane austen and charlotte bronte to the silent fate of shakespeare’s gifted (imaginary) sister and the effects of poverty and sexual constraint on female creativity.

virginia woolf (1882-1941) is regarded as a major twentieth-century author and essayist, a key figure in literary history as a feminist and a modernist, and the centre of ‘the bloomsbury group’

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
at a hearing before the senate judiciary committee, christopher wylie described discussions at the company about suppressing the vote, exploiting racial tensions, and testing campaign slogans in 2014 for use in the 2016 election. - one of the things that did provoke me to leave was the beginnings of discussions of voter disengagement, i have seen documents reference and i recall conversations that it was intended to focus on african-american voters. the company learned that there were segments of the population that responded to messages like ‘drain the swamp’ or images of border walls or indeed paranoia about the ‘deep state’ that weren’t necessarily reflected in mainstream polling or mainstream political discourse that steve bannon was interested in to help build his movement.

jon sharman
the independent

text:
innocence, happiness, unconditional smiles and bright colours are something that is becoming rarer in our society. 
but this little sweetheart was walking and running the streets relentlessly, spreading colours and smiles already with her presence. and then she asked us to buy these colours and her smile was just undeniable. i felt blessed that i was able to meet this happy little angel.
and the reason i'm sharing this is because everywhere i go i see people complaining, or frustrated or nagging or distracted and depressed.
why are we so negative, if we are able to see every little negativity why can't we see every little positivity
let's start a hashtag and create a happy community where we realise how much colourful life actually is and how much beautiful you are. 
#metoohappy 
i'm not negating the seriousness or need of #metoo campiagn but just wished to counter the negative stories with a little spark of positivities and also some how i think that sharing stories as a victim is kinda overrated let's be our own armies and discuss what happens then .
.
.
.
.
.

text:
15. thankful for everyone who stands up against fascists, and fights against the normalization of hate. 
16.  especially thankful to all those that came out to vote in this last election (or tried to, only to be turned away/denied this basic tenant of democracy), because who we elect reinforces what type of people we want to be, and i for one vote for kindness and love.
17.  thankful for a new era of discourse.  where previously subjects have been deemed "too impolite" for general conversation, the #metoo movement, and the #blacklivesmatter movement has insisted that we do.  has shown us what it looks like when these topics are brushed under the rug, how women continue to be met with disbelief, their rape kits left untested.  and how easily "blue lives" legislation gets passed while black people continue to be murdred by the police without cause, and without repercussion.  what you think is important, it determines how you treat the rest of the world.  so i am grateful for this #honesty, and this #truth, and #hopeful for the potential impact on our collective future. 
#gratitudes #givingthanks #standup #fightback #ideas #thoughts #thismachine #woodyguthrie #quotes

text:
i was given this book by a girl who was in my #iop (intensive outpatient) after an unsuccessful suicide attempt. that happened in december 2016. i didn't get sober until the beginning of 2018. i didn't enjoy the early months of sobriety. it wasn't until after my stroke that i really started living my best life!!! i had always talked about it. i posted inspirational quotes and watched #tonyrobbins blah blah blah. but it wasn't until after the strokes that i remembered #brenebrown - she gets it. she understands shame, guilt, the pressures of being a mom in today's world. she gets it. i believed her and i am so grateful to these amazing women in my life today, who aren't afraid to recover out loud. .
.
.

text:
5 strawberries 
1/2 banana
1 cup sparkling mineral water
4 ice cubes
*
this was so good!!! i learned that if you blend the carbonated water in parts it won’t explode when you open the blender top. i took the strawberries and a third of the water and blended that first. then i added the banana and the next third to the blender and combined that. lastly i added the remaining carbonated water with the ice. no mess and it was delicious 😋 *
today the girls and i had a busy morning. productive and busy. i realized my car needs more work than i thought and just in time for the holidays! boooooo 👎🏼
*
i think i stressed about it for an hour or so and then i decided to let it go. it goes to the mechanic on monday and what will be will be. in the meantime i have my girls, my boys will be here soon, and there are white fudge oreos in the cupboard. i’m thankful ☺️
*
day 321 is in the books...❤️❤️

text:
the time i became a feminist...
.
.
people often ask me what made me so passionate about women’s empowerment and ending gender-based violence and to be honest i’m not really sure.  maybe it was the day i became a father to a little girl and i knew i couldn’t save her from a patriarchal society.  maybe it was the day my closest loved ones and friends disclosed to me they were sexually assaulted and felt like no one would believe them.  maybe it was when i worked as a volunteer coordinator for a domestic violence/sexual assault center and heard the countless stories of trauma from survivors and their loved ones.  maybe it’s when i look out today and see that the majority of crime and violence against women is committed at the hands of man.  to be honest i can’t say when i became so passionate about this. .
.
passion is a funny thing because some folks can pin point a time and place when they got passionate about an issue or cause but i can’t think of one moment.  i can only see a collection of moments and things and people that have made me passionate about ending gender based violence.  and you don’t have to have a daughter, and you don’t have to know someone who’s been assaulted (although it’s very likely you do), and you don’t have to work at a sexual assault/domestic violence center to be passionate about women’s empowerment.  because the truth is...it’s something we all should be passionate about. ✊🏾💜👸🏽 .
.

text:
the last two years i have worked hard at reinventing myself. 
stripping off the old self... the fear 
the doubt
the shame 
the beliefs 
the mindsets 
the toxins 
the people / relationships

and began to build a new me from the ground up 
by the grace of god... new relationships 
new mindsets
new boldness
new beliefs 
new surroundings 
new strength 
a new future 
a new business 
there has been a lot of change !! all of this transitioning took daily effort, daily intention, and daily pain. 
but because of all the work i have put in, today at 31, i have never felt more confident in who i am and the plans god has for me. 
i didn’t realize the shot gun decision to chop my hair off last week played into all of this. it was one of the few final pieces to severing ties with my past. 
but dang it has been liberating !!!!! i am reminded that we should not wrap our identity up in our image. 
i am reminded our fear is the only thing stopping us from moving from good to great. 
i am reminded that moving into who we are called to be is uncomfortable. 
but most of all 
i am reminded that ugly ends, 
really means, 
a beautiful new beginning!! 🖤

text:
história são fatos e realidades; e para se explica-la ou justifica-la a ferramenta utilizada é a ciência. esta contribui e faz parte até hoje do nosso dia-a-dia. nos trazendo o poder do conhecimento de forma generalizada.

é através da ciência que nos tornamos mais conscientes e livres para criarmos a nossa propria estória. quando compreendemos o nosso lugar na natureza e no cosmos, a criatividade da mente transcede.

o entendimento sobre a evolução humana desperta a livre vontade (liberdade) de ser, o livre arbítrio; proporcionando com que a auto-aceitação seja um caminho mais transparente, deixando de ser tão complicado ou confuso.

caso fosse dado hoje o total poder do conhecimento e a liberdade de ser à todos, ainda assim não conseguiriamos explicar o comportamento mental do ser humano de hoje.

a ciência proporciona a expansão do conhecimento, o entendimento de si mesmo e do mundo ao nosso redor. no entanto, a moralidade chegou para literalmente atrapalhar deixando o ser estagnado. sabe por que? porque a moralidade ela não tem nada haver com fazer o bem; seu único objetivo é dizer aos outros o que fazer. sejamos menos julgadores, caso queira, aplique em voçê desmistificando o que lhe foi passado e busque o conhecimento e estudo. afinal todos nós quando nascemos somos ateístas, sem exceção.

história é construída através de fatos e não de opiniões.

#mulher #mulheres #empoderamento #forçanaperuca #somosfortes #equalidade #feminismo #amorpróprio #ciencia #estudo #metoo #eutambém #respeito #amor #amorpróprio #autoaceitação

é através da ciência que nos tornamos mais conscientes e livres para criarmos a nossa propria estória. quando compreendemos o nosso lugar na natureza e no cosmos, a criatividade da mente transcede.

o entendimento sobre a evolução humana despea a livre vontade (liberdade) de ser, o livre arbítrio; proporciodo com que a auto-aceitação seja um caminho mais transparente, deixando de ser tão complicado ou confuso.

caso fosse dado hoje o total poder do conhecimento e a liberdade de ser à todos, ainda assim não conseguiriamos explicar o compoamento mental do ser humano de hoje.

a ciência proporciona a expansão do conhecimento, o entendimento de si mesmo e do mundo ao nosso redor. no entanto, a moralidade chegou para literalmente atrapalhar deixando o ser estagnado. sabe por que? porque a moralidade ela não tem nada haver com fazer o bem; seu único objetivo é dizer aos outros o que fazer. sejamos menos julgadores, caso queira, aplique em voçê desmistificando o que lhe foi passado e busque o conhecimento e estudo. afinal todos nós quando nascemos somos ateístas, sem exceção.

história é construída através de fatos e não de opiniões.

text:
help @heather.patterson1986
. 
there were 3 officers within a year and a half time frame that used their position for personal / sexual gain towards me while at work and on duty. i was manipulated, pressured, coercive, and frighten to work, because of retaliation or repercussion while at work and many more emotions that i can’t express at this time.
i got termination at work over these officers and they didnt, because of the 3rd officer who was really aggressive towards me at work and was able to get me alone in a modular during work and sexually assault me after i expressed i didn’t want to do anything at work. a few days after the incident it was reported by a family friend. who i expressed my feeling to his wife about the situation at work. an investigation was started and i was interview about the situation. there were questions i didn’t answer truthfully, because i was coached and threaten by the officer, but i was very truthful about what happened on company grounds. after the investigation the officer found out what happened and instantly freaked out and started calling and texting threatening me to go back and retract my statement, because he’s an office and better not lose his job over me or else.
being afraid i did what he said and retracted my statement the following day. i was asked why during the 2nd investigation interview and i said, “i just made up the story.” it made me look really stupid and made me feel very helpless, because i didn’t know what to say or do being in that situation. after approximately a two and half years of a so called investigation i was let go from a career i invested 10 years with and known as a good and hard working person  for falsifying serious claim against an officer.
right now i feel like a woman with no voice... no one wants to listen to me. all they say is" you shouldn't have put yourself in that position". i was threaten and feared for my life!!!. i am beyond pushed to my limits and i really need "help"!...
#helpme #feminist #womenempowerment #supportus #rapevictim #abusesurvivor #needhelp #lgbtq #metoo #justice #feminism #slutshaming #genderequality

text:
resultatet från vår omröstning baserat på tidigare inlägg;
majoriteten av oss upplever inte att vi får vår röst lika hörd som de vita hörs, vilket är det vi upplevt och sett, och vill arbeta emot.
 85% anser att vi ska ha en egen plats inom metoo rörelsen och till sist så röstade 29% för en gemensam kamp och 71% för egen kamp.

nu tänkte jag lite på varför det ena måste utesluta det andra, jag tänker att låta poc ha en egen plats inom metoo behöver väl inte vara synonymt med att vi för separata kamper, utan att folk faktiskt uppmärksammar den dubbla utsatthet vi lever i, för vi inte bara blir utsatta för sexuella trakasserier generellt, utan att vi också blir utsatta för dessa trakasserier med rasistiska undertoner, där våra kroppar blir översexualiserade, fetischerade, exotifierade och faktiskt ofta sätta i mindre värde än den vita kroppen.
dock anser jag att när det gäller en gemensam kamp att vita öppnar upp rummen för oss, att de tar till sig av den kritik poc för gentemot vit feminism och inser att vi går igenom olika kamper och de behöver backa oss och inte försöka förminska det vi säger om de stora klyftorna.
detta appliceras självklart även på nbpoc, då vi har privilegier över svarta, och vi ska lyssna på deras kritik gentemot oss i frågan.

text:
in jan this year a psych panel declared malka leifer unfit to stand in court. in feb, only a few days later, leifer was arrested on fraud charges. 
between april and november there were 18 court dates regarding jail, bail, almost home detention, and new psych assessments. 
now as the momentous year draws to a close we head off to israel to face our former school principal in a court room for the first time. 
au revoir australia! 
a huge thank you to a very generous anonymous donor for funding our flights to israel! -
-
malka leifer, my former school principal was living as a free woman in israel, claiming mental illness in order to avoid extradition. 
meanwhile in australia she has 74 charges of sexual assault and rape to face with numerous victims waiting for justice.
for more information visit my facebook page. link in bio.

text:
at a hearing before the senate judiciary committee, christopher wylie described discussions at the company about suppressing the vote, exploiting racial tensions, and testing campaign slogans in 2014 for use in the 2016 election. - one of the things that did provoke me to leave was the beginnings of discussions of voter disengagement, i have seen documents reference and i recall conversations that it was intended to focus on african-american voters. the company learned that there were segments of the population that responded to messages like ‘drain the swamp’ or images of border walls or indeed paranoia about the ‘deep state’ that weren’t necessarily reflected in mainstream polling or mainstream political discourse that steve bannon was interested in to help build his movement.

jon sharman
the independent

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
dieses buch geht unter die haut ! in „nein“ schildert winnie m li die geschichte einer vergewaltigung aus sicht des opfers und des täters. es ist, leicht fiktionalisiert, ihre eigene geschichte. wie anmache in sexuellen gewalt umschlagen kann , wie es dem opfer bei den polizeilichen und medizinischen untersuchungen ergeht, wie im kreuzverhör des verteidigers im prozess , wie sehr das leben sich verändert.... all dies erzählt winnie m li klar , ehrlich und schonungslos. ein wichtiges buch , das die ohnmacht gegenüber gewalt aufzeigt , den langen weg zurück in das leben, ein leben , das nicht mehr von dem begriff „opfer“ geprägt sein will. 
winnie m li isr harvard absolventin reiseschriftstellerin , filmproduzentin und programmmanagerin einiger filmfestivals. ihr buch wurde mit dem „not the booker prize“ 2017 ausgezeichnet. übersetzt hat den bei arche erschienenen roman volker oldenburg. ein hartes, ein wichtiges buch !!! #nein #winniemli #metoo #metoomovement #sexuellegewalt #vergewaltigung #bookstagrammer #bookstagram #buchtipp #mustread #belfast #london #wanderung

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian
