millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
this is the moment an irish mp held up a lace thong in parliament after a man was acquitted for raping a 17-year-old.

in the trial, the victim’s underwear was shown in court sparking outrage. 
the defence lawyer argued the teenager consented to sex because "you have to look at the way she was dressed. she was wearing a thong with a lace front." the controversial case led to mp ruth coppinger holding up a lace thong in parliament and women sharing pictures of their lacy underwear with the hashtag #thisisnotconsent condemning victim shaming.

protesters took to the streets to say clothes are not consent.

taoiseach leo varadkhar said: “nobody who is a victim of sexual violence, nobody who is a victim of rape, is ever to blame for the crime inflicted on them, i believe that any defence on those lines is absolutely reprehensible”

text:
dear humans 
i’m here waiting in the dark for you, i know everything about you, i don’t need to chase you, i’m waiting for you to walk in my path, it’s the path most people will walk down, i’m here waiting for you to walk over me, but when you do it will be like walking on quick sand. you could spend many years with me. 
i will hold my hands around your mouth so no one can hear you, i will take you to the bottom as i do, you will meet my cousin anxiety,
who will scare the living day lights out of you.

you will lose sleep over me, you will start to lose hope whilst you’re stuck with me. i will isolate you, you will just want to sleep when you’re with me.

only in your mind, you will
finally work me out 
who am i ?

text:
the ideas inherent to prostitution are a kind of get out of jail free card for all men. those ideas deem women to be unworthy of economic resources without providing men with sexual access, and that underpins male dominance. and that is why the denial must be so strong. if we can deny the agony that harriet went through in prostitution to keep a roof over her head, it’s easy peasy to deny the pain of the young researcher who faces losing her job unless she sleeps with her revolting boss.

if we open ourselves to this everyday pain, we are confronted with the awful reality of how commonplace it is for men to buy young women to do the things that harriet describes.

text: this (not in particular) bitch has been such a factor in my whole upbringing and life. this bitch made me starve, made me expel, even made me monitor for years. this bitch, she ruled me without me even realizing. this bitch held me at a “max.” at a “standard.” she keeps me grounded and that hold over me had me almost at the max effect than a lot of things and even people i’ve met within the last 10yrs w the same issues. and not just weight but as females w any uneasiness in anything physical or mental whatsoever. we aren’t just forced upon these stigmas. we also aren’t just women. we’re men too. you can think “oh just these girls dressing this way” or oh these “people i’ve known from hs” or “this bitch i knew a while ago who could’ve gotten down” or “this seemly precious baby who’s just starting off in the real world” (highlight a style or not but honestly) #weightlosstransformation #weightlossjourney y’all great for feeling so great. y’all great for loving and indulging in a better opportunity and all around well-being of life. but this bitch, she holds me close and keeps me there. this bitch can’t stand to let me go. this bitch rules my world and i’m sorry but she has a say. i pray for the day i can ignore the hunger or ignore even the shame that comes w seeing that specific number. i don’t disrespect or try to compare me to you. but for me personally, it eats at me continuously and it’s tough. i’ve never been diagnosed and i’m not sporting mental illness. i’m just coming forward w what kind of weighs at me and makes me down sometimes. i love you all, all shapes and sizes. help others and help yourselves. i came to this realization in a women’s bathroom revolving around compliments that i guess this is me asking for love and to love those around me regardless of whatever thing they could be experiencing. goodnight my babies 💖 #eatingdisorderrecovery #nomorebinging #selfcare #selflove #selfreminder #wecanrelax #metoo #bulimiarecovery #pdd text:
i have married men in my messages, thanking me for the red pills. they often say the same thing “i would like or comment on the page but my wife would see it.” what a sad way to live for any man, looking in the mirror realizing that you are a shell of yourself.

marriage makes a man docile because they have to walk on egg shells since the wife has big daddy government on her hot line. a man holds all the power in the relationship until he marries. once he says i do, that power is transferred to the woman, and she now controls every aspect of his life. i was recently having some drinks with a few buddies and one of them (married one) got a call from his wife. he said “i know i told you i would be home at 1, but me and the fellas hanging can i hang a few more hours”. her response was no, come home immediately. so he finished his drink and left home. i'm the only red pilled guy of the group, so i kept my thoughts to myself, but in my head i was thinking, man this guy gives her a comfortable lifestyle, they travel, she's a housewife and wants for nothing, yet she still speaks to him like he's the servant. the other guys who are in relationships sort of chuckled cuz they go through the same shit.

men have been conditioned to be servants to their women to the point they laugh and chuckle about their servitude. the sad part about it is knowing that every woman has the potential to be the servant to her man, they just treat their man according to his worth and value and many men undervalue themselves.

it makes me so happy seeing all the support i've got in less than 24 hours on my tiny little initiative/campaign- #stopthisshit

i am calling out again, to everyone who's game to join this 'cleanliness drive'. 👷‍♀️👷‍♂️ while there are many more internet platforms other than social media where harassing parasites could be taking shelter and multiplying, i am trying to solve it for social media because that's where i have personally come across the 'message requests' horrors. 💭think about it, aren't these creeps the potential sexual harassers and probably are already raping out there? or eve teasing on streets everyday? i am from delhi and it sucks knowing that i've grown up knowing defense mechanism against teasers in public places, roads, transport, everywhere! i breaks my heart reading rape news everyday and a lot of them are in delhi. 💭

.
jag vill i detta inlägg påminna om att den även rör ganska mycket vid ämnena missbruk i familjen/hur det är växa upp som maskrosbarn samt hur det är att vara barn/anhörig till en föräldrar som drabbas av och dör i cancer. boken har alltså en ganska bred målgrupp och jag skulle vilja påstå att den passar alla i alla åldrar samt både män, kvinnor och alla andra.
.

text:
communiqué : tariq ramadan remis en liberté

https://www.partiantisioniste.com/articles/communique-tariq-ramadan-remis-en-liberte.html

hier, jeudi 15 novembre, l’intellectuel musulman tariq ramadan, mis en examen pour des viols qu’il conteste, a clamé son innocence devant la cour d’appel de paris, chargée de statuer sur sa mise en liberté.
après 9 mois d’incarcération et le rejet de quatre demandes de remise en liberté surveillée, la justice a finalement accédé à la requête émise par la défense de l’islamologue suisse, ordonnant sa mise en liberté sous contrôle judiciaire, a annoncé son avocat, me. emmanuel marsigny, à l’agence france-presse (afp).
« c’est une décision logique dans la mesure où les derniers développements du dossier apportés contre lui étaient mensongers. il n’y avait plus d’obstacles à ce qu’il soit libéré », a déclaré ce dernier à l’issue de l’audience publique.
la libération de tariq ramadan est soumise au versement d’une caution de 300 000 euros, alors qu’il devra également remettre son passeport suisse, aura l’interdiction de quitter le territoire, d’entrer en contact avec les plaignantes et certains témoins et pointer une fois par semaine au commissariat.
mis en examen pour des soupçons de viols sur deux femmes, tariq ramadan a clamé jeudi avec force son innocence lors de sa première apparition publique depuis son incarcération. « j’irais fuir où ? alors que tout va vers mon innocence. je vais rester en france et défendre mon honneur et mon innocence », a-t-il déclaré depuis le box, ajoutant « je veux bien qu’on me reproche d’avoir menti pour protéger ma famille, ma fille qui est dans la salle. mais qui a menti le plus ? qui a instrumentalisé le mouvement #metoo ? », accusant ses accusatrices de se répandre dans les médias.
après avoir nié pendant des mois tout rapport physique avec les deux femmes, l’islamologue avait fini par reconnaître avoir «menti » mais avait démenti tout viol.
le parquet général, qui avait requis le rejet de la demande, n’a donc pas obtenu gain de cause. cette décision de la chambre de l’instruction intervient alors que les confrontations entre tariq ramadan et ses deux plaignantes principales ont déjà eu lieu, ren

text:
#bookreviewsbyzinnia
.
circe, by madeline miller
genre: fiction, greek mythology, fantasy
🍃
a story of greek gods, myths and magic. the centre to this novel is circe, the sorceress and daughter of helios. she was able, by means of drugs and incantations, to change humans into wolves, lions, and swine.
🍃
when circe discovers her powers, she commits a wicked act and is then banished to an island. what follows then is an account of her life on this island. there isn’t a plot, but a series of many incidents and how multiple gods, mortals and myths are weaved into her life. the narrative is very compelling and keeps you hooked right till the end.
🍃
to me this book was a psychological analysis of a women. the character of circe is so endearing. she is aware about her powers and that she  isn’t the greatest. she faces ostracism, insult, abuse and more hate... yet she has streaks of humility and sympathy. she continues to take control of her destiny and define her life. i definitely don’t take this as a weakness of women, but rather her power to engulf all the negativity and still be steady, resilient and empathetic. however i wished the author showed an equal balance of aggression in circe’s character. there was action, i expected slightly more.
🍃
while this may be about gods, there is a lot of humanity in there. it makes you realise the mortality of humans. through daedalus’s character, author symbolises the satisfaction one gets by creating their own things, doing things by hands rather by the powers of magic.
🍃
the narrative is very relevant and strikes a chord with many things of our world today - the gap between powerful and powerless, ugly nature of politics, the way the women are treated and revelations with #metoo ... and more. clearly a reader can read it at many different levels.
🍃
simple story, powerful narrative, poetic and engaging throughout... must read. taking one star away because i wished there was a bit more writing about other characters.
🍃
rating: 4/5
🍃
fav #bookquotes .
‘humbling women seems to me a chief pastime of poets. as if there can be no pastime unless we crawl and weep’
.
#circe #madelinemiller #greekmythology #fantasy

text:
i read this morning that the 17-year-old girl who's underwear was used as a scapegoat into clearing her attacker of all rape charges, killed herself. 
not only was she brave enough to relive every teeny tiny detail of her ordeal in the sheer hope she could sleep at night as her attacker would at least be paying a fraction of the price for what he had done - but she was then mocked, humiliated and told her choice of underwear was to blame. 
can you even imagine how scared she was? how alone she must have felt? 
end the victim blaming. teach men and women and all children about consent, respect and boundaries. 
end sentences and statements like "there's more to this story" "well, she could have done this", " if she/he had down that..." rape. is. rape. 
#thisisnotconsent #metoo #surviors #women #love #fight #fem

text:
hello, everyone.  my name is richard santiago and i’m contacting you to share a film i’m working on about my good friend, a register nurse, jason b. almeida. jason was a young man who committed suicide after years of workplace bullying.  this film documents his life and heartbreaking death.  we are doing a world-wide premier of this teaser trailer on nov. 21st 2018, to help launch the gofundme page we’ve created to complete this film.  we are also launching a page on our website,  http://www.thebullyexposed.com/jasons-story/, to offer perks for those who donate to help us complete this project.  please share this post and link to all your friends and family.  help us tell jason’s story.

don’t just share this post one time. please share it every wednesday to honor jason’s life. keep sharing until the project is funded.

check out these videos to learn more about our project to honor jason:

dear bully pitch video
https://vimeo.com/300931778  dear bully teaser:  the jason bennett almeida story
 https://vimeo.com/300930280

the bully exposed gofundme page
https://www.gofundme.com/telljasonstory 
film perk page
http://www.thebullyexposed.com/jasons-story/

thebullyexposed.com is a 501 (c) 3 non-profit group and all donations are tax deductible.

text:
why the #metoo movement has been one of the biggest threats to reasonable analysis in the past decade -
•
#metoo movement perhaps has done some good, but it is beyond conceivable that it has done more harm. 
there is no reasonable social scientist who does or will ever form judgements about our civilization based on this movement.
•
simply put, you cannot predicate your judgement on the number of tweets that have #metoo in it.
•
firstly, you do not know whether you are dealing with an unbiased sample space.
•
secondly, accusations do not necessarily represent the truth.
•
thirdly, if a person has been harassed, the rational course of action is to go to law enforcement. after the matter has been investigated, if there is any party guilty, they receive punishment according to the legislation.
•
metoo movement, however, is impulsive and believes in following none of the steps necessary for conducting a broad scale multivariate social analysis. basically, it's a very very poor (and illogical) representation of a what is going on.
•
that being said, your iq has to be under 72 in order to think that since i do not support the #metoo movement, i am okay with sexual harassment.
•
anyone with sense knows that sexual harassment is not even in the slightest sense acceptable behavior. 
so, to everyone out there playing the group identity game; sorry, but if a person does not support the #metoo group, that does not mean they support the sexual assaulters.
•
stop breaking the world into victims and oppressors, thinking the victims are not capable of any bad and the oppressors are not capable of any good. //
name: The Critic

text:
tuesday, november 27th at the university of minnesota, in concert with a panel of nonprofit leaders from around the twin cities, the kelly nicole foundation proudly presents an unforgettable evening of music, film and inspiration.  join us for an artistic exploration of overcoming shame featuring music by the late artist, kelly nicole and the award-winning documentary on her battle with a trauma-based eating disorder.  inspired by the lyric "it's all my fault, but i'm not to blame," the panel will take audience questions, so we want to hear from you.  bring a friend and join the conversation.  free food, great music and film.  walter library 402, november 27th at 5:30pm.  visit kellynicole.com for more information on the music behind the mission.  admission will be free.  survivors will be heard.

#amplified #kellynicolefoundation #hatebecoming #ptsd #trauma #metoo #edrecovery #eatingdisorderawareness #music #film #art #mentalhealth #umn #universityofminnesota

text:
"i think this picture resembles you." that is the message that was sent to me from one of my relatives last month, a week before i spoke at the ywca network luncheon. it hurt my feelings and i tried to tell myself that this relative was just joking, etc. however, you know when someone isn't playing and we've never "played" like that before. so instead of letting it discourage me, i used that energy to bring my all to the delivery i had the following week.

my point is victim shaming and victim blaming is a real thing. this picture just takes me back to a time in my adolescence where though no harm was intended, the mythology of some family members was to tell me i'm ugly because of the choices i was making at the time. eventually, it stopped, and instead i was told that i was "acting ugly." i realize for me victim shaming and victim blaming started years and years ago when i was sexually assaulted by one of my relatives best friend's _____. no punishment was brought about, the situation by some was minimized, and i was treated like it was my fault for being, "flirty," and you go wow! at the age of 9. seriously! 
anyway, i've decided to use my voice in a way to instruct, so from today until january, whenever i experience shaming or blaming i'm going to post a picture of myself wearing the t-shirt i had designed on this topic. awareness is everything. some people don't understand the hurt and destruction they cause. here we go... #domesticviolencesurvivor #domesticviolence #metoo #indianapolis #empowering #survivor #healing #author #authorlife #goodreads #indy #indieauthor

text:
tuesday, november 27th at the university of minnesota, in concert with a panel of nonprofit leaders from around the twin cities, the kelly nicole foundation proudly presents an unforgettable evening of music, film and inspiration.  join us for an artistic exploration of overcoming shame featuring music by the late artist, kelly nicole and the award-winning documentary on her battle with a trauma-based eating disorder.  inspired by the lyric "it's all my fault, but i'm not to blame," the panel will take audience questions, so we want to hear from you.  bring a friend and join the conversation.  free food, great music and film.  walter library 402, november 27th at 5:30pm.  visit kellynicole.com for more information on the music behind the mission.  admission will be free.  survivors will be heard.

#amplified #kellynicolefoundation #hatebecoming #ptsd #trauma #metoo #edrecovery #eatingdisorderawareness #music #film #art #mentalhealth #umn #universityofminnesota

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
female journalists of bangladesh gathered today, in front of the national press club, to stand in solidarity with those sharing their #metoo accounts of sexual abuse, from different sectors of work and life.

among them was tasnuva anan shishir, of the national human rights commission and a member of the trans community. she shared an account of being called to discuss a job offer at a publishers office in dhaka, where he locked the door, forcefully kissed her and then exposed his genitals to her. upon threatening to scream, he let her out of the office room.

several other accounts have been publicly shared recently. #metoobangladesh

#bodbetii

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
tuesday, november 27th at the university of minnesota, in concert with a panel of nonprofit leaders from around the twin cities, the kelly nicole foundation proudly presents an unforgettable evening of music, film and inspiration.  join us for an artistic exploration of overcoming shame featuring music by the late artist, kelly nicole and the award-winning documentary on her battle with a trauma-based eating disorder.  inspired by the lyric "it's all my fault, but i'm not to blame," the panel will take audience questions, so we want to hear from you.  bring a friend and join the conversation.  free food, great music and film.  walter library 402, november 27th at 5:30pm.  visit kellynicole.com for more information on the music behind the mission.  admission will be free.  survivors will be heard.

#amplified #kellynicolefoundation #hatebecoming #ptsd #trauma #metoo #edrecovery #eatingdisorderawareness #music #film #art #mentalhealth #umn #universityofminnesota

text:
tuesday, november 27th at the university of minnesota, in concert with a panel of nonprofit leaders from around the twin cities, the kelly nicole foundation proudly presents an unforgettable evening of music, film and inspiration.  join us for an artistic exploration of overcoming shame featuring music by the late artist, kelly nicole and the award-winning documentary on her battle with a trauma-based eating disorder.  inspired by the lyric "it's all my fault, but i'm not to blame," the panel will take audience questions, so we want to hear from you.  bring a friend and join the conversation.  free food, great music and film.  walter library 402, november 27th at 5:30pm.  visit kellynicole.com for more information on the music behind the mission.  admission will be free.  survivors will be heard.

text:
“i’m tired of people not taking sexual harassment as a serious issue. it is” - eva gutowski
.
.
bener nggak sih, masih dapat dibilang seriiing banget kita lihat orang-orang yang menganggap pelecehan seksual itu bukan hal yang seharusnya dianggap serius? bahkan “catcalling” aja atau mungkin buat cewek-cewek yang suka sendirian jalan di pinggir jalan terus ada yang manggil “mbak cantik, kok sendiri aja” atau “ih sombong banget mbak cantik nggak mau noleh”, masih sering dianggap hal yang wajar. dan masih banyak kasus-kasus pelecehan seksual yang kerap terjadi di sekitar kita, tapi kita nggak menyadari itu atau bahkan kita menyadarinya namun kita nggak berani atau bingung untuk lapor ke siapa.
.
sudah banyak gerakan-gerakan di seluruh negara yang dibuat oleh para korban yang sudah gerah untuk tinggal diam tentang pelecehan seksual yang terjadi terhadap mereka, contohnya adalah gerakan #metoo. namun, dengan banyaknya gerakan dan kampanye tentang kasus ini, masih selalu ada aja kasus-kasus pelecehan dan kekerasan seksual baru yang terjadi belakangan ini. apa sih sebenarnya yang salah?
.
hal ini memang sangat melelahkan, sesuai dengan quote di atas. tapi apa kita harus diam terus kalau ada kejadian pelecehan seksual di sekitar kita atau terhadap diri kita sendiri?
.
selalu ingat, untuk kalian perempuan maupun laki-laki, pelecehan seksual fisik bahkan verbal adalah sebuah kejahatan serius yang harus ditindak. seperti yang udah tabu jelaskan kemarin, kalau kalian mengalami pelecehan seksual, tunjukkan kalau kamu nggak suka dan jangan tersenyum/tertawa karena itu dapat dianggap “consent” oleh pelaku! kalau kamu ngerasa nggak nyaman, maka katakanlah demikian!
.
tabu

#breakingthetaboo #breakingthestigma #sexed #sexeducation #pendidikanseks #kesehatanseksual #kesehatanreproduksi #tabu_kekerasanseksual #tabu_sexualviolence

text:
pre-holiday tip 3....."laps are for napkins".....
when families gather, there is often a tendency for adults to engage the children, and there is nothing wrong with this. however, predators can use this as an opportunity to touch and fondle children by doing what on the surface appears innocent and loving, such as having a child sit in their lap. one of our supporters recalls how her godfather would have her sit on his lap as a child and he would stick his hand down her pants. this would be while they were in a room full of people, yet no one ever seemed to notice. so, while it seems extreme to some to say a child shouldn't be allowed to sit in the lap of another adult, keep in mind that the actions and behavior patterns of a predator are far from "normal" and while you may never think of doing such heinous things to a child, molesting children is all they think about. we have to be sure not to provide opportunities for them to do so. #childsexabuseawareness #stopchildsexabuse #childsexabusesurvivor #parentsofchilldsexabusesurvivor #sexualassault #endchildsexabuse #endrapeculture #childabuse #sextrafficking #atlanta #atl #georgia #women #girls #teens #awareness #sexcrimes #rapevictims #rape #victims #children #prevention #trafficking  #survivor #tips #blogger #speaker #metoo #advocate

text:
okay y'all. snuggle up with some coffee bc this is a long post. not too long, because if you know me, you know i hate feelings posts. whatever. it's my birthday. just read it.

about two years ago, i started a whole new chapter in my life. i decided to be the fearless boss bitch my mom raised me to be. i decided to be my own boss and open up a bridal salon.

to those who have always known me...not a surprise. i've always loved weddings. and bridal fashion. i don't know why. wasn't raised to. i just do.

but here's what not everyone knows. about six years ago, i was forced into the unfortunately large #metoo club. it stripped away the confidence and pride i was born with. it shattered relationships and hurt people.

after that happened, i found myself running away to chicago to start fresh. new school, new goals, new start. i was going to be a journalist. 
well, it wasnt the right career for me, as much as i loved it, but it did give me time to reset. 
after i realized maybe i wouldn't be a journalist, i took the first decent job that would pay me. i had to pay some freaking bills, okay? it was there that i learned i wanted to be my own boss and do things my way. it was the tipping point to finding my voice again.

i left that job and jumped into the weird world of weddings. it's where i learned you can have a career that makes you happy. i have to thank my friends and coworkers at alfred angelo and betsy robinson's for that. 
but now i'm ready. now we get to the end of the story. today, i'm announcing that i'm finally stepping into the role i've always belonged in. very soon, i will be opening @lauraandleighbridal in cherry hill, nj!

look out because here i come!! afterword:

i want to extend special thanks to the people who have really made this happen. @lyndacalderone for being my rock, my momvestor and confidant in all this. you're the reason this is happening. @don_calderonee my partner and best friend. @georgerweber the one who pushed me to get out there and just fucking do this already. my dad, @ralph.calderone, who advised me every step of the way. 
keep following our journey!

text:
"it shouts at me in dreams", you did this to yourself', 2011.

culturally, i think we in the west are largely comfortable with 'survivor stories'. the narrative since #metoo has been that a silence has been broken. but history shows us that survivor stories have been part of the media for a long time (in magazines, on tv chat shows). our focus on the survivor correlates with the focus on the complainant in sexual violence trials where the person to whom sexual violence has happened is often cross examined at great length - sometimes longer than the defendant(s). does our cultural lack of focus on perpetrators create the conditions for a misplacement of focus and interrogation in the court room?

text:
its important to remember that it’s okay to not be okay. there are going to be days where moving forward seems impossible. there are so many resources and people out there to talk to.  i encourage you to find that one person to open up to whether it be a councillor in person or an anonymous online/mobile councillor, a friend, a family member, a teacher etc. you never have to go through anything alone there is always someone you can talk to. it is extremely important to create a support system to help you back on your feet, and begin your recovery and healing. .
.
acknowledge your accomplishments and be proud of what you do during the day. it doesn’t have to be big things it can be as simple as getting out of bed in the morning. living with the burden of sexual assault is psychologically draining and damaging, but, it does not define you, and does not need to consume you. #believeinyourvoice .
.
.
.

text:
tuesday, november 27th at the university of minnesota, in concert with a panel of nonprofit leaders from around the twin cities, the kelly nicole foundation proudly presents an unforgettable evening of music, film and inspiration.  join us for an artistic exploration of overcoming shame featuring music by the late artist, kelly nicole and the award-winning documentary on her battle with a trauma-based eating disorder.  inspired by the lyric "it's all my fault, but i'm not to blame," the panel will take audience questions, so we want to hear from you.  bring a friend and join the conversation.  free food, great music and film.  walter library 402, november 27th at 5:30pm.  visit kellynicole.com for more information on the music behind the mission.  admission will be free.  survivors will be heard.

text:
ever since #metoo campaign started, it was only the celebrities or those connected with cinema, politics and journalism were raising their voices. we wanted to know the opinion of a common man working in different fields about sexual harassment faced by a commoner. 
the simple ballot box poll was held during the cats blood donation camp held on 12th of october at chandigarh. participants in the poll were the blood donors, volunteers, visitors as well as the blood bank staff. participants were  18-57 years of age and represented everyone profession from a coo to a car park attendant. 
wonder what do you make of this simple on-the-spot #metoo result.

text:
words from co-founder @spiritualheart to all the men who are afraid to commit to one partner, believe that committed relationships are a trap, or have a pattern of infidelity or abandoning good relationships whenever their partner calls them forward in honesty and accountability. and yes, it goes both ways but this is for the men who have these patterns.⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣
as men one of the most important lessons for us to grasp in life is that a committed partner who truly loves us as we are and yet continually challenges us to step deeper into our power, is a treasure to cherish with all our heart. not only will they feel like home but they will inspire us to actualize our full potential. yet, we will never be able to grasp this lesson and honor a partner who is devoted to us if we haven't invested the necessary time and energy into healing our subconscious wounding and re-parenting our inner boy.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
if we haven't healed our wounding and found love and compassion for our inner child, then our hearts will remain blocked with emotional debris and our mind clouded with illusions which we may be almost completely unaware of, but which will weigh us down nonetheless by keeping us repeating unconscious patterns which harm ourselves and others. we will know if our vital energy isn't flowing freely through our heart because it will build up in our head or in our genitals, manifesting as an overactive monkey mind or overpowering lust, both of  which limit our freedom.⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣
i've found through my own process of healing and liberating myself from addictions, that holding space for my inner boy and opening my heart was a crucial part of connecting to my anima - my inner feminine nature. as men, developing a relationship to our anima is necessary if we are to grow in wholeness so that we may embody our masculine power. because if we don't have a relationship to our own inner feminine principle then we will forever feel half empty and seek to fill that emptiness from outer validation.⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣
once we heal the wounding which prevents us from opening our heart we will discover that love is the power which tames our animal nature and calms our mind. when our heart has 👇🏾👇🏼👇
name: MASCULINE ALCHEMY + EMBODIMENT

text:
“period girl” the documentary, is now going to be a feature film!
.
as some of you may know, my soul-sister @jalena.kl has been making a documentary about my year off from harvard to keep growing @periodmovement and publishing my debut book #periodpower ❤️ well, #periodgirl was just picked up by @stickfigureproductions to become a feature! stick figure is known for their production of @stepthemovie, and has received an oscar nom, sundance special jury prize, and multiple emmy’s — so, we’re in good hands. 🎥
.
to be honest, it doesn’t feel like a documentary is being made about me right now because jalena and i have become such close friends i don’t notice that sometimes she has a camera out. so, this is going to be a very candid and honest look into my life, and i’m nervous but very excited to share it with you. 🍿
.
proud of you @jalena.kl , humble and honored to have the opportunity to work with you, and excited to get to know the rest of your team @alanasiq @guccidavy @helenacyau @breaktide 🌊
.
photo by @ariaherbst 📸
name: Nadya Okamoto

to be honest, it doesn’t feel like a documentary is being made about me right now because jalena and i have become such close friends i don’t notice that sometimes she has a camera out. so, this is going to be a very candid and honest look into my life, and i’m nervous but very excited to share it with you. 🍿
.
proud of you @jalena.kl , humble and honored to have the opportunity to work with you, and excited to get to know the rest of your team @alanasiq @guccidavy @helenacyau @breaktide 🌊
.
photo by @ariaherbst 📸

text:
after you leave an abusive, toxic person, never believe their false promises and charisma they use to get you back. remember how many times they said they would change their behavior and treat you right? remember how many times that promise broke? remember how many times you cried yourself to sleep, alone? remember how many times you felt trapped? how it felt like you were dealing with dr. jenkel and mr. hyde? remember how it felt to not be able to do or say anything right. how you kept giving them chances only to be disappointed later. remember the times you were ignored for days on end with no explanation? remember the unfaithfulness and lies? remember the name calling and the bombardment of insults thrown at you. remember the walls getting punched and getting screamed at? 
remember all the pain, loneliness and sadness they gave you. 
don’t believe their apologies and their façade. you are not a toy to be put down and picked up when they are bored. you are human and are full of purpose. 
people do not change. i waited 3 years for that person to change and it only got worse and would have started to get physical if i had not of left when i did. i am so grateful i was able to get out. 
do not waste your time with people who have crushed, poisoned and tortured your love. 
you saw the real them they hide behind close doors. 
they do not deserve your presence. 
keep building on your self love and self empowerment. 💪 #empowerment #selfcare #selflove #leave #nevergoback #abuse #domesticviolence #awareness #toxic #people #tattoo #woman #selfie #selfportrait #makeup #makeupartist #loveyourself #womenempowerment #metoo #strength #letgo

text: in the aftermath of the #metoo movement i am pulled to begin the conversation of what it means for men, what they have learned, what women have learned, what women desire, what men desire to learn, have meaningful dialogue about masculinity, and see what we can change and recover together. at the masculinity paradox training in nyc with @estherperelofficial i felt the need to bring the genders together and do the work to dismantle our conditioned internalized beliefs around masculinity (all genders have these beliefs and we can let go of them). i feel that we should work together to heal rather than point fingers and say ‘you change!’ we all need to change. dm me for details for the wednesday bimonthly in person dayton -group process on the masculinity paradox. #daytonohio #dayton #counseling #masculinity #troubleshooting #relationships #relationshipgoals❤️ #therapysession

i'm waving at you from my beautiful, bright, positive and bright world whilst you  scuttle back to your dark hate filled place from whence you came.

this quote says it all for me !

text:
hi! 🙌there are quite a few new people around here so i just wanted to do a lil introduction post for those of you who don’t know me! 
my name is hannah michelle, i’m 23, and i currently live in brooklyn, ny but i was raised in los angeles, ca. 
i started “cats calling back” as a response to how i was internalizing the street harassment i was experiencing on the streets of new york. it was breaking me down, and i knew i had friends struggling with it as well, so ccb was born out of that need to do something. the rage was motivating, and the community and support that have come out of the fruits of that rage have been so inspiring and incredible. ccb aside, here are some juicy tidbits about me:
1.i have a bfa in musical theatre. yup. you read that right. i grew up acting, singing, and dancing!
2.i love jazz. a lot. also my brother @aaronprovisor is a brilliant jazz pianist. art and music run in the family, but he’s the genius one. 
3.i can put both of my legs behind my head. there was a vaudeville contortionist somewhere in my family at some point. 
4.literally 90% of my clothes are from thrift stores. like really is there anything better than someone complimenting your outfit and then being able to say you got it for 3 bucks at a goodwill? (also one time i bought a shirt from a goodwill and then literally saw it on betty cooper on riverdale soooo) 
5.my girl gang keeps me sane and i would actually probably be dead if it weren’t for them. y’all know who you are. (special shout out to @vivian_fabulous who took these photos!) again, thank you for all who have read, participated in, and supported cats calling back and myself. i’m so excited to see where this all goes. ❤️
as always, send your stories to catscallingback@gmail.com or dm me. •

text:
hej mitt underbara linkedin nätverk!

vilken underbar helg detta har varit på nowwhat och oj vad jag har lärt mig massor!! har lärt mig följande saker:

1. jag kan lägga upp en bra affärsidé som vårat team tyckte om.

2. jag kan vara team manager och product manager samtidigt!! och fick höra av två personer som driver ett eget bolag att jag har den förmågan och att jag ska satsa på det🙏🤩 3. stå på scenen och prata om våran produkt. och fick några beröm att jag hade en fantastisk röst som var tydlig när jag pratade på scenen!

4. att få vara med härliga personer utvecklare, designer och skapa något helt magiskt vi gjorde detta tillsammans. och känslan att få jobba med nya människor och göra något viktigt för #metoo 
5. jag har äntligen hittat min sista pusselbit i min karriär och det är att jag kan kasta in mig i två roller och göra ett jobb på 3 dagar för att jag ville utveckla mig vidare.

6 fick även rekommendation att kontakta bonniers tech👍

men även om vi inte vann så vann vi något helt annat och det är kunskaper och se vad jag och våran grupp kunde åstadkomma 💖 
och detta är jag mest stolt över!

sist men inte minst vill ni ha en driven person som mig på erat bolag ring då mig!

i'd really like to participate in @i_weigh, an idea set up by @jameelajamilofficial to replace numbers of weight and stuff like that with positive, other things to describe yourself. 
i'm non-binary, autistic, abrosexual, disabled. 
i'm a sexual assault survivor and i deal with ptsd every day. 
i am a sibling and a cousin. i'm a friend and i am someone who makes mistakes but learns from them. i'm an active member of multiple organisations striving to help others.

text:
at a hearing before the senate judiciary committee, christopher wylie described discussions at the company about suppressing the vote, exploiting racial tensions, and testing campaign slogans in 2014 for use in the 2016 election. - one of the things that did provoke me to leave was the beginnings of discussions of voter disengagement, i have seen documents reference and i recall conversations that it was intended to focus on african-american voters. the company learned that there were segments of the population that responded to messages like ‘drain the swamp’ or images of border walls or indeed paranoia about the ‘deep state’ that weren’t necessarily reflected in mainstream polling or mainstream political discourse that steve bannon was interested in to help build his movement.

jon sharman
the independent

text:
after midterm election results #trump characterized as ‘historic’ and 'very close to complete victory’… there now is not one #republican house representative from #reagan country.
actually the long-anticiptaed #bluewave happened.
along with control of the house came pick-ups of 7+ governorships and scores of crucial statehouse seats nationwide. and as final results continue to come in, #democrats keep on winning. stop! please! democrats… i’m getting tired of so much winning!...
the work of the people has been on hold for two years because the current house has been working for only one person… #illegitimate #failingpresident #donaldtrump.
mark your calendars… come january 3, the forwarding of legislation that the american people deserve and need — will resume. bill after bill will pass in the house… and be sent on to the senate — where, sure, senators can vote them all down — but at their own peril. those running for re-election to the upper chamber will need to explain to 2020 voters why they voted against so may popular and sensible reforms.
also resuming — long overdue oversight... corruption. ethics. russia. kavanaugh. tax returns. …you name it… now we can really start getting to the bottom of it. 
on election day we took the first big step to save #america… now we must end the gop protection and enabling of the unindicted co-conspirator in the oval office: investigate… #trump #russia #washingtondc #lovetrumpshate #dumptrump #nevertrump #msnbc #cnn #foxnews #moveon #trumpprotest #notmypresident #politics #journalism #indivisible #makeamericagreatagain #maga #plannedparenthood #womensmarch #crazytown #metoo #resist

text:
at a hearing before the senate judiciary committee, christopher wylie described discussions at the company about suppressing the vote, exploiting racial tensions, and testing campaign slogans in 2014 for use in the 2016 election. - one of the things that did provoke me to leave was the beginnings of discussions of voter disengagement, i have seen documents reference and i recall conversations that it was intended to focus on african-american voters. the company learned that there were segments of the population that responded to messages like ‘drain the swamp’ or images of border walls or indeed paranoia about the ‘deep state’ that weren’t necessarily reflected in mainstream polling or mainstream political discourse that steve bannon was interested in to help build his movement.

jon sharman
the independent

text:
sobre nuestra portada en facebook para el #25n 🦋🦋🦋 25 de noviembre, el origen del día mundial contra la violencia machista, clara muestra de que las mujeres pelearon por sus derechos históricamente. la fecha tiene origen el 25 de noviembre de 1960, ése día fueron asesinadas tres hermanas:  minerva, patria y maría teresa, conocidas como las "mariposas", fueron combatientes activas contra el régimen del dictador dominicano rafael trujillo, quien ordenó su asesinato.

las mariposas no fueron un símbolo al azar para identificar esta fecha y a ellas. bajo el nombre secreto de "mariposas", las tres hermanas se identificaban entre la resistencia.

la ejecución se produjo cuando las luchadoras antitrujillistas regresaban de visitar a sus respectivos esposos en la cárcel san felipe, de puerto plata. allí cumplían su condena, habían sido encarcelados y ellas decidieron ir a visitarlos a pesar de que sus vidas estaban en peligro.

dos de las hermanas, minerva y maría teresa, fueron encarceladas, violadas y torturadas en varias ocasiones, una de ellas en la cárcel la victoria.

cuando volvían de visitar a sus maridos, las mandaron a matar haciéndolo pasar como un accidente, aunque el pueblo dominicano no lo creyó, a pesar de que los titulares de los diarios así lo afirmaron.

la historia de estas valientes mujeres que pelearon contra trujillo se convirtió en un símbolo de resistencia contra el machismo.
desde 1981, el movimiento feminista latinoamericano reivindica esta fecha como un día de lucha en contra de la violencia machista. ¡síguenos en facebook!

text_retweet:
fortfarande nästan exakt ett år efter att den första delen i elsa-serien kom ut så ramlar det in recensioner. och jag blir precis lika glad nu som när den första recensionen kom. tack bettans boktips🌸
#detmåstegå #dekommerändåintetromig #sexuellaövergrepp #gymnasiet #hoiförlag #ungdomsroman #högstadiet #metoo #böcker 
#repost @bettansboktips with @get_repost
・・・
📚📚
titel: ”de kommer ändå inte tro mig”.
författare: ulla m. nissen
📚
elsa har flyttar och börjar på en ny skola. en fest ska hållas och för att kunna gå på den så ljuger hon för sina föräldrar att hon ska på tjejmiddag. på festen dras hon in i ett rum av en kille. elsa blir paralyserad och stänger av övergreppet. efteråt skäms hon. allt är hennes fel.
📚
en mycket viktig bok som jag hoppas att många läser, både yngre men även äldre. ett sätt att sätta sig in i hur tonårsflickor kan känna sig och hur de klandrar sig själva. så frustrerad jag blev, ”anmäl honom!!”. men hur gör man, som vän när man får höra något hemskt som hänt? hur pratar man som förälder när man ser att ens barn inte mår bra? så många frågor som väcktes. tyvärr en verklighet hos allt för många tjejer, hur de trycker ner sig själva och anser att något fruktansvärt som hänt är deras fel. jag blir så ledsen, och frustrerad, och arg. en mycket viktig bok! läs den som förälder och diskutera med andra föräldrar, och tonåringar, både tjejer och killar.
@u.m.nissen har skrivit en blandvändare om ett tungt ämne men blandar det med en fin berättelse om vänskap och tonårsförälskelse 💕
betyg: 4 / 5 #dekommerändåintetromig #ullamnissen #tonårsbok #hoiförlag #viktigbok

en mycket viktig bok som jag hoppas att många läser, både yngre men även äldre. ett sätt att sätta sig in i hur tonårsflickor kan känna sig och hur de klandrar sig själva. så frustrerad jag blev, ”anmäl honom!!”. men hur gör man, som vän när man får höra något hemskt som hänt? hur pratar man som förälder när man ser att ens barn inte mår bra? så många frågor som väcktes. tyvärr en verklighet hos allt för många tjejer, hur de trycker ner sig själva och anser att något fruktansvärt som hänt är deras fel. jag blir så ledsen, och frustrerad, och arg. en mycket viktig bok! läs den som förälder och diskutera med andra föräldrar, och tonåringar, både tjejer och killar.
@u.m.nissen har skrivit en blandvändare om ett tungt ämne men blandar det med en fin berättelse om vänskap och tonårsförälskelse 💕

text: trigger warning: #metoo “how did you get started?” as makers, we are often asked that question. and usually, it’s not a simple answer. i think i’ve always been a maker and i have a garage and closets full of hobbies that i’ve tinkered with that prove this theory. as for paper flowers, the project featured here started it for me. last year at just about this time my good friends at @gracelessmedia asked me to create a piece with them in response to #metoo. graceless asked their readers to share their experiences with us and we used their words to help shape the art. i had a vision of a beautiful woman but as you got closer you saw that she was actually filled with memories and messages (written on dirty, ripped paper) of hurt, shame, abuse. we showed this piece, called layers, at the east austin studio tour 2017 and asked the viewers to share their stories with her. write it on a paper flower petal and tuck it into her skirt or crumple it up and bury it deep inside of her. i never could have imagined how this piece was received by the public. both women and men were moved to tears. mothers and daughters writing on petals side by side. wordless nods and tearful hugs from those who were grateful to be able to share, maybe for the first time, “i’ve never told that to anyone before.” open conversations with young sons about new vocabulary words seen on the dress. i’m not sure if i will ever work on anything as important and personal as this project. it was an honor and a privilege to bring even a tiny amount of healing to my community. thank you to @gracelessmedia  @lisakettyle @wandering_chick  @voguevignette (for the ah-mazing illustration that still makes me cry) and everyone who helped and interacted with our little project.
name: Kerry Joyce

text:
➰ embrace yourself

this can be challenging in times of ig and the body shape that is socially seen as beautiful. this can be easily misleading; leading away from who you really are. yes, i love beauty, sensuality and aesthetics. i love authentic beauty and the confidence that comes with having arrived within. 🦋 a journey to experience yourself. the path of self discovery. 🦋how far have we come as women? too many still exposing their intimacy feeding the patriarchal view in times of #metoo . or covering yourself up in a veil. same same. too many hating their body fed by which pictures in society? a picture made up for consumption mostly; wanting you to believe you need to buy make-up to be beautiful. i also like make up and i like for the most part being natural. cover models, actresses and newly influencers are the role models put up to imitate; especially young women. what kind of body image are we still supporting? how free do you feel from this? is this empowering women? are we still not good enough and need another career title, more education, need to be thin, have this brand and that house? who is it who wants to suck up all your energy, strength and wisdom? what game are you buying in and what for? the #shakti energy moves the universe. our womb is our center of creation. our feminine energy is powerful and therefore has been suppressed. more and more women are awakening. ➰➰➰ can you love yourself in your body? can you respect yourself how and who you are? can you feel well and put your real wellbeing first? what is left when you see yourself naked? raw as you are. on good days and not so good days. self esteem and dignity for a deeper balance. beautiful connection and experiences with humans sustain everyone of us. nothing is more valuable than sth that touches and feeds the soul with loving values. these experiences build a foundation of trust and love for us and our children we always remember and carry us through life. 
#speakyourtruth #igch18 #beauty #beautyfull #realbeautystartswithyou #wordstoliveby #flyingyoga #photography_amore #expandingyourinnerpeace #ig #embraceyourself #respect #dignity #wellbeingwarrior #wellbeing #feminine #zhiim

#repost @warif_ng with @get_repost
・・・
what happens to a rape survivor  when she seeks help on the streets?
.
.
abaad, a lebanese ngo, conducted a social experiment to see how bystanders would react.

an actress played the role of a rape survivor seeking help in public. these are the real reactions she got.
blaming the survivor is still very prevalent in our society today’, it could have happened anywhere and the reactions would still be the same. 
we need to do better as bystanders so that women and girls can live in a society free from rape and sexual violence.

text:
самое популярное слово 2018 года!

назвал оксфордский словарь. им стало слово toxic — «токсичный». его употребление за год увеличилось на 45%, почти в два раза. люди называют токсичными отношения, культуру, политику и ч̶ё̶р̶т̶о̶в̶ы̶х̶ ̶м̶у̶д̶а̶к̶о̶в̶ других людей.

на звание самого популярного также претендовало слово incel — «воздержание», сокращённый вариант involuntary celibacy, обозначающее невольное воздержание от сексуальных отношений из-за стеснительности, физических недостатков и когда тупо не с кем. похоже, человечество стремительно двигается к роботам 🤖

также в топ попало слово gaslighting — «газлайтинг», обозначающее форму психологического насилия, при которой жертва начинает думать о себе как о ненормальной, психически неадекватной личности. на газлайтинге построены #книга и фильм «исчезнувшая» и ещё «девушка в поезде». читали? смотрели? 👀

а вот по версии издательства harper collins словом 2018 года стало single-use — «одноразовое использование». исследователи утверждают, что употребление этого слова увеличилось в четыре раза за последний год. они связывают это с ростом спроса на одноразовую посуду, из-за чего экологи вновь забили тревогу ☢️ слово «одноразовый» обогнало по популярности слово vegan — «веган» и хештег движения против домогательств #metoo — «я тоже».
.
кстати, один фотограф как-то решил наглядно показать, как страдает планета от засилья одноразовой упаковки и 4 года не выкидывал мусор, потом рассортировал его по видам и сделал фотографии. за это время он накопил около 70 кубометров мусора, а именно 1600 бутылок из-под молока, 4800 втулок от туалетной бумаги, 800 килограммов газет. как-то многовато, не?) 🙄 по его задумке, снимки должны внушать ужас и заставить людей задуматься. вот этот наивный парень @antoinerepesse.

а для вас какое слово стало самым популярным в 2018 году? маты тоже можно (нет!) 😁

на звание самого популярного также претендовало слово incel — «воздержание», сокращённый вариант involuntary celibacy, обозначающее невольное воздержание от сексуальных отношений из-за стеснительности, физических недостатков и когда тупо не с кем. похоже, человечество стремительно двигается к роботам 🤖

также в топ попало слово gaslighting — «газлайтинг», обозначающее форму психологического насилия, при которой жертва начинает думать о себе как о ненормальной, психически неадекватной личности. на газлайтинге построены  и фильм «исчезнувшая» и ещё «девушка в поезде». читали? смотрели? 👀

а вот по версии издательства harper collins словом 2018 года стало single-use — «одноразовое использование». исследователи утверждают, что употребление этого слова увеличилось в четыре раза за последний год. они связывают это с ростом спроса на одноразовую посуду, из-за чего экологи вновь забили тревогу ☢️ слово «одноразовый» обогнало по популярности слово vegan — «веган» и хештег движения против домогательств  — «я тоже».
.
кстати, один фотограф как-то решил наглядно показать, как страдает планета от засилья одноразовой упаковки и 4 года не выкидывал мусор, потом рассортировал его по видам и сделал фотографии. за это время он накопил около 70 кубометров мусора, а именно 1600 бутылок из-под молока, 4800 втулок от туалетной бумаги, 800 килограммов газет. как-то многовато, не?) 🙄 по его задумке, снимки должны внушать ужас и заставить людей задуматься. вот этот наивный парень ntoinerepesse.

а для вас какое слово стало самым популярным в 2018 году? маты тоже можно (нет!) 😁

text:
vertical talent agency is happy to announce their newest client, mi chelle nessk.

michelle nessk is an award-winning indie filmmaker and artist. michelle's full feature film, o. unilateralis, was named as the "all-time best-found footage film" by gunaxin magazine.

michelle is also known as zee monsta, the horror host and creator of horrors of the pnw, the annual horror anthology showcase that premieres every year at crypticon seattle. michelle's production company, gloomy sunday productions, helps produce and create films with aspiring filmmakers. michelle also owns the indie horror publication the blood shed. michelle utilizes these outlets to help fellow indie filmmakers pursue their dreams.

michelle is active as a host and liaison for various charities, events, and community outreach for children and survivors of domestic violence, most recently partnering with love horror for their louder than wolves event to benefit my sister’s house.

booking for 2019: verticaltalentagency@gmail.com #foundfootage #foundfootagehorror #horror #scary #bloody #metoo

in roman law, rape could be committed only against a citizen in good standing. the rape of a slave could be prosecuted only as damage to the owner's property. people who worked as prostitutes or entertainers, even if they were technically free, suffered infamia, the loss of legal and social standing. a person who made his or her body available for public use or pleasure had in effect surrendered the right to be protected from sexual abuse or physical violence.⠀
⠀
read further on the history of rape culture and how women have always been suspect of some degree of acquiescence, and how rape trials have focused on the victims having to prove their innocence and lack of consent, more than determining the accountability of perpetrators in the blog: “actresses in the history of rape culture”: https://buff.ly/2dkmdou⠀

text:
yeah, probably crying for the same boyfriend, who tried to force us in bed. and, if he weren't my boyfriend but/and a rapist, you'd not just blame me for the act, but probably get me married off to him, right!? so this entire thing got me thinking how marital rape is not criminalised in our country, which is why victims are forced to get married to the assaulter/rapist. thus, by this act of reciprocation, they legitimise the entire act of assault. well done!
not to forget, my own father said, "you want to get famous in the whole #metoo time, which is why you're telling us now, that you were in 6th grade when your tutor tried to exploit hou, sexually."

text:
"tenía 12 años. es mucho más fácil sonreír y decir que no te pasa nada que que te están violando." estas son las duras palabras que la exgimnasta gloria viseras ha concedido al periódico digital @eldiarioes sobre las violaciones de las que fue víctima en su infancia.

la exdeportista denunció a su exentrenador jesús carballo 32 años después de sufrir agresiones sexuales durante su época de competición entre los 12 y los 15 años. "cuando estás lista para denunciar, judicialmente es tarde’’, dice.

a pesar de que el delito había prescrito y era consciente de que no se podía ir a juicio, ya que los hechos ocurrieron a finales de los setenta, en 2012 decidió denunciarlo ‘’para proteger a otras niñas y niños, a mis hijos". al poco tiempo, él fue retirado de la federación de gimnasia.

actualmente colabora en el proyecto de ley de protección frente a la violencia en la infancia y en la campaña 'empezar a hablar' promovida por el comité ministerial del consejo de europa. 
se trata de acciones muy necesarias desde el punto de vista de @latarjetamorada, pues el abuso es una lacra presente en el mundo del deporte que hay que combatir con medidas de prevención y respuesta contra los abusos sexuales en menores.

text:
alright y'all. gonna feel myself for a minute, because this is so cool! until august of this year (in the top photos), i thought i had straight hair with occasional waves, but thanks to accidentally not combing my hair after washing it one september day, i found out i *might* have my mother's curls. since then i've been following the #curlygirlmethod and being regimented about not damaging my hair - though i've never straightened it before - and voila! transformed and transforming all while feeling more joyous and more like myself each and every day.

there are times when this daily ritual feels superficial, but all that's been happening in the world - be it election season, mother nature breaking, the outpouring of #metoo testimonies in the musical world i once called home or the antics of cheeto in chief - has taken a toll on my mental health and emotional/creative capacity. spending a few minutes each day undoing the damage of years of conditioning around hair texture and embracing my natural curls has been bizarrely healing on multiple levels. here's to truth, self care, little joys and continuing to constantly revolutionize and question both internally and externally!

also, gratitude for @slroper8 who constantly pushes me to be truthful, outspoken and radically myself! 🖤✊🏽

#repost @workingclasshistory ・・・⁣
on this day, 18 november 1965, the term “sexism” was probably coined by pauline m. leet during a "student-faculty forum" at franklin and marshall college. ⁣
⁣
“sexism” appears in leet's forum contribution "women and the undergraduate", and she defines it by comparing it to racism, stating: "when you argue... that since fewer women write good poetry this justifies their total exclusion, you are taking a position analogous to that of the racist—i might call you in this case a ‘sexist’... both the racist and the sexist are acting as if all that has happened had never happened, and both of them are making decisions and coming to conclusions about someone’s value by referring to factors which are in both cases irrelevant." ⁣
⁣
worker co-ops are essential to the fight against patriarchy, as they create a workplace with structural accountability. furthermore, with every individual being an owner as well as an employee, there is far less room for intimidation, threats of unemployment, etc. pictured: women protesting against sexual violence in india⁣

text:
last night was the first time in my life that a man could have taken advantage but instead he proved to me that i could be totally vulnerable while looking super sexy and i wouldn’t be taken advantage of or abused... as sad as that sounds, it was one of the greatest gifts i’ve ever received and my heart is warm today, so filled with joy, relief, ease and love... because i was shown truly good, honorable men exists. 
i had to share this because i belong to the #metoo group and i battle to trust, in fact being able to trust someone has often felt like a nice fairytale... and so to all of you “#metoo” members who have lost hope, i want you to know there is hope, there are good decent trustworthy men in this world. 
break the abusive cycle and be open to the possibility that they exist, focus on attracting them into your life. you deserve to be treated with kindness, compassion, gentleness, love and respect. 
today is a new day and i welcome it with calm, relief and contentment. my heart is warm. thank you kind friend for changing my world 😊🙏🏼🌟 life happens and incidents create beliefs. our beliefs and thoughts shape our reality and we so desperately want to be right all the time... but sometimes when we are proven to be wrong, a ripple effect of healing flows through our being and we become armed with a more powerful belief that 
transforms our lives from that moment on.

remain open, it can lead to the greatest gifts that life can bring.

#metoo #newme #new #newbeginnings #beginagain #love #compassion #trust #respect #care #relief #calm #belief

news release: tariq ramadan released

18 november 2018 ￼yesterday, thursday november 15, the muslim philosopher tariq ramadan, indicted for rapes he contests, claimed his innocence before the paris court of appeal, responsible for ruling on his release.

after 9 months in prison and the rejection of four applications for release on probation, the court finally granted the request issued by the defense of the swiss islamic figure ordering his release under judicial supervision, said his lawyer, emmanuel marsigny to the france-presse agency (afp). “it’s a logical decision as the latest developments in the case against him were misleading. there were no more obstacles to his release,” said the latter after the public hearing.
the release of tariq ramadan is subject to the payment of a 300,000 euros deposit, while he must also surrender his swiss passport, will be prohibited from leaving the territory, to get in touch with the complainants and some witnesses and to come once a week to the police station.
charged with suspicion of raping two women, tariq ramadan claimed his innocence in his first public appearance since his incarceration on thursday. “where would i go when my innocence is being accused? i will stay in france and defend my honor and my innocence,” he said, adding” i want to be reproached for lying to protect my family, my daughter who is in the room. but who lied the most? who exploited the #metoo movement? accusing her accusers of spreading things in the media.
after months of denying any physical relationship with the two women, the islamic figure eventually admitted to having “lied” but denied any rape.
the public prosecutor’s office which had requested the rejection of the application was therefore unsuccessful. this decision of the investigating chamber comes as the confrontations between tariq ramadan and his two main complainants have already taken place, thus making the argument of the risk of pressure less solid.
moreover, according to his lawyer, mr. marsigny, the recent sms files on file wou

text: admittedly, it took some time to learn how to pronounce her name correctly, and it’s such a beautiful one too. aja sax resides in toronto, and has been in f&b for 18 years - a crusader for knowledge and transparency in our industry. “i’m concerned diners don’t understand the business side of restaurants – between the public and industry. there’s constantly ‘contention’ to deal with – over tipping, high food cost, outrageous hospitality expectations. […] our industry should be more transparent so that general public can see what really goes into the service and product you’re paying for.” aja is definitely an activist in our industry – as soon as something – good or bad – occurs, she’s right there examining the facts, and posting thought-provoking content on social media to get the discussion rolling. aja has been successful in bringing quite a few issues to light in the past, and so it’s no surprise that she wants to sit with martin luther king jr. and pick his brain, “how did he turn his passion into a movement? how was he able to push forward, break down walls, and maintain empathy for the cause in the face of so much evil?” recalling a lot about “what people are made of” she thinks back to her 16 year old self, and offers some advice, “you know, if you save all those tips, you can probably set yourself up for a much better future”. bringing information to the people, aja was so close to studying journalism in the past, but she doesn’t seem to need it. these days, she’s still passionate about food, wine and beverage, cherishes those perfect moments with guests at the bar, or in her yoga classes where she can dig deeper, and make an impact. “i don’t want much, i just want more” says aja, and considering she’s ‘all in’ for things she fundamentally believes in, we can expect a lot more noise when she gets her hands on it. #minibarleadingladies

text:
so, i have been holding back in creating my first online course - but the calling is becoming louder and louder...
six years ago, life was great i was working for a swiss investment bank in the heart of the city of london, i had been working in wealth management for over 10 years, wealth management is basically helping the 1%, the rich get richer. nothing wrong with that and i am grateful for my career but i wanted to have a life with more meaning. it was an august afternoon in 2012, life was good and  i was feeling blessed 😇 . i got down on my knees and said a prayer of gratitude straight from my heart and asked god to show me how to do his work. the very same day, i was drugged and ******** assaulted by a work colleague (#metoo) 😞and it sent my life into disarray. i experienced very dark times with depression, ptsd, anxiety - the works.  during this time, even though i couldn't understand why i went through the incident that i did, i kept my eyes 👀 on god and miraculous things started to happen before my eyes. from supernatural experiences caught on dvd, to the manifestation of much needed money 💵 within seconds of praying about it, to the prayer 🙏🏽 i said before going to sleep one night that saw me wake up to stock (from my side hustle) that had been sitting around for 5 years suddenly get bought by an #abc us sitcom to be a part of their set!.
i know that what i have been through cannot be in vain and i want to share what i can and empower who i can. •
•
•

i am therefore launching a 6 week live online course. •
•

#rebalanceandrevive: “master the power within to overcome life's obstacles, so you can upgrade your future and thrive in all that you do in 6 weeks’’ •
•
•

as the course is live, spaces will be limited. 
please send me a dm for further info. •

let’s see if we can rebalance & revive your life too. 🎉🙌🏽💕🙏🏽
name: Rebalance & Revive ™️

text: my heart aches as i read the news of your passing. @evas_wish is the very first page i followed when @empower.thepowerful was born. smack bang in my face & heart your message hit me right in that place. i remember coming across your profile and thinking how can such an amazing human exist. you are the definition of humanitarian, serving your heart, time and spirit to people all over the world. if you guys don’t know much about eva’s story she has been battling terminal cancer for many years and devoted all of her time to bring awareness to sexual trauma. fundraising thousands for this much needed cause. eva developed a crisis line and online messaging systems for survivors to utilise here in nz also *amazing*. you will remain in a pure and deep part of my heart always. your memory will continue to live on as part of empower the powerful’s great inspiration. much aroha, gratitude, love and appreciation to you sweet angel. aroha nui, kaity xxx

text_retweet:
👏👏👏👏 #repost @strongwoman_cassiiieeee
・・・
“you have to look at the way she was dressed. she was wearing a thong with a lace front.” last night i stood and looked in my underwear drawer. thongs, g strings, knickers and of course i have my fair share of big comfy pants. some are lacy, some are sparkly, some are mesh, silky, patterned or just plain old granny boring. i bought them because i liked the fabric, or the colour, or the print. or they looked comfy. or because i had a bra that they would match. 
never did i ever stand in a shop to consider my new knickers and think, “but will i get myself raped in these though?” the lawyer representing a man acquitted of raping a teenager in court advised that the jury should consider the underwear worn by the 17-year-old girl as evidence. (she was wearing a lace thong and therefore must have been totally asking for it?!)the 27-year-old man was found not guilty by the jury of eight men and four women.

i can’t actually comprehend that in 2018 this is still allowed to happen in a courtroom. i’m sad that it seems zero lessons have been learned since lindsay armstrong took her own life, following the degradation she experienced while her underwear was paraded during the court case of her rapist. he was found guilty. she and her family served the life sentence. 
let’s not kid ourselves that rape is anything to do with attractiveness or seductiveness or sexy underwear. rape is about power and control. rapists are to blame for rape. 
what the survivor wore, drank or covered their crotch with that day is fucking irrelevant. #thisisnotconsent

@supamanhiphop: to dance is to pray, to pray is to heal. some things are written in the stars. i shot this video in less then one minute and wanted to put @bearfox34  song sung by teio swathe over it. on impulse i dedicated it to our missing and murdered indigenous women. so many people have been touched by this video that was created with only good intention to bring awareness to #mmiw and people who have lost loved ones. it got nominated for a nammy and i didn’t encourage anybody to vote for it but it won. so if it brings more awareness to the epidemic that is happening to our indigenous sisters and people, it is a good thing! a’ho! #mmiw #supaman #illuminatives #indigenouswomen #missingpeople #bringbackoursisters #nativeamerican #firstnations #healing #supersoulsunday #sundayfunday #nativeamericanheritagemonth #indigenous #praisedance #metoo #believesurvivors #nativewomen #missing

text:
the purpose of the #metoo movement is to create meaningful change. i introduced the empower act to help address sexual harassment in the workplace. 
empower act quick facts:
-prohibits nondisparagement and nondisclosure clauses that cover workplace harassment
-establishes a confidential tip-line
-requires that public companies disclose the number of settlements, judgments, and aggregate settlement amounts in connection with workplace harassment
-prohibits companies from tax deductions for expenses and attorneys’ fees in connection with litigation related to workplace harassment
-requires development and dissemination of workplace training programs to educate at all levels about what constitutes prohibited workplace harassment

text: pictured here, #goodgirlsrevolt author @lynnpovich and i talking at a @weareavodah symposium on jewish women's leadership hosted by @bam_brooklyn. for those who don't know of povich, in 1970 she and 45 other women at @newsweek filed a landmark gender-discrimination lawsuit that pretty much paved the way for whatever rights we broads have in the workplace today. it was an honor to talk about feminist strategy and organizing, #metoo, and internal and external glass ceilings with this woman who's as brilliant and kind in person as on the page; i’m grateful to organizer @kirablayne for enlisting me. one big takeway: "you can't legislate attitudes, so when pushing for change you have to come to the table as a collective with very clear asks." a vital message for all social justice warriors. #powerinnumbers #jewishbroadview #bruchabruja
